# RDFS Schema for Business: Staffing Hr

@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix ind: <http://datamodel.lakehouse.org/business/staffing_hr#> .

# --- Root Business Class ---
ind:Business rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label 'Business' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Root class for all business entities' .

# --- Specific Business: Staffing Hr ---
ind:StaffingHr rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Business ;
    rdfs:label 'Staffing Hr' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Staffing and Human Resources is a workforce solutions industry providing temporary and permanent talent placement, recruitment process outsourcing, workforce management, and HR consulting services across all industries and skill levels.' .

# --- Domain Classes ---
ind:Candidate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Candidate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all talent supply-side identity and qualification data. Owns candidate profiles, resumes, skills inventories, certifications, work history, availability, preferences, sourcing channel attribution, and candidate engagement records. Supports ATS workflows in Bullhorn and drives talent pool management, redeployment, and bench tracking across all placement types (W-2, 1099, EOR). Tracks candidate status from initial sourcing through placement and beyond.' .

ind:Client rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Client' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all client (employer) identity and commercial relationship data. Owns client company profiles, contacts, account hierarchies, locations, MSA agreements, rate cards, VMS integrations, SLA configurations, NPS scores, and CRM engagement history sourced from Bullhorn and Salesforce. Serves as the authoritative source for WHO the business serves on the demand side, supporting both direct clients and VMS/MSP program relationships.' .

ind:Recruitment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruitment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns the end-to-end talent acquisition and sourcing lifecycle. Covers sourcing strategies, job posting, sourcing campaigns, candidate submittals, right-to-represent (RTR) tracking, client interviews, interview scheduling, offer management, hiring decisions, and QoS (Quality of Submission) metrics. Tracks recruitment KPIs such as time-to-fill (TTF), time-to-start (TTS), submittal-to-hire ratios, and fall-off rates. Integrates with Bullhorn ATS and supports RPO and MSP delivery models.' .

ind:Joborder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Joborder' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all client requisitions (reqs) and job order demand data. Owns job order headers, position requirements, skill specifications, headcount targets, duration, bill rates, pay rates, markup percentages, SLA commitments, TTF and TTS targets, and fulfillment status lifecycle. Tracks the complete job order lifecycle from intake through closure including extensions, modifications, and cancellations. Central operational hub connecting client demand to candidate supply.' .

ind:Placement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Placement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns the full placement and assignment lifecycle for both temporary and permanent hires. Manages temporary assignments, contract-to-hire, temp-to-perm, and direct hire placement records. Tracks assignment start/end dates, extensions, backfill tracking, conversions, conversion fees, job details, work location, supervisor, fall-off rate monitoring, redeployment events, and assignment status. SSOT for active worker assignment status connecting candidates to job orders.' .

ind:Timesheet rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Timesheet' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all worker time and attendance data for contingent workers. Covers daily timesheet submission, hours worked, approval workflows, overtime (OT), double-time (DT), breaks, absences, PTO usage, per diem tracking, schedule management, and labor hour records sourced from Kronos Workforce Ready. Captures billable hours for client invoicing and payable hours for worker compensation. Feeds payroll processing and client billing with authoritative hours data.' .

ind:Payroll rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Payroll' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all worker pay and tax processing data. Covers gross pay calculation, pay rates, gross-to-net calculations, tax withholdings (FICA, FUTA, SUTA), burden rates, deductions, net pay, workers compensation insurance premiums, W-2 and 1099 tax form processing, payroll tax filing, PTO accruals, and benefits administration processed through TempWorks Payroll. Handles multi-state payroll compliance and supports EOR and co-employment payroll models.' .

ind:Billing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all revenue and financial transaction data. Owns client invoice generation, bill rates, spread calculations (bill rate minus pay rate), markup calculations, gross margin tracking, payment terms, accounts receivable, payment processing, collections, credit memos, and dispute management sourced from Salesforce Revenue Cloud and Oracle NetSuite ERP. Supports various billing models including hourly time-and-materials, per-diem, project-based, SOW-based, and direct placement fee billing.' .

ind:Compliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns regulatory and legal compliance data across the entire workforce lifecycle. Covers I-9 verification, E-Verify, EEOC compliance and reporting, OFCCP reporting, FLSA worker classification determinations (W-2 vs 1099), co-employment and joint employment risk management, non-compete and NDA enforcement tracking, OSHA safety compliance, audit trails required by DOL, OSHA, and IRS regulatory frameworks. Ensures all placements meet federal, state, and client-specific compliance requirements.' .

ind:Credentialing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Credentialing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all candidate credential, certification, license, screening verification, and qualification data. Covers BGC (Background Check) results from Sterling, drug screen outcomes, professional license verification, skills assessments, training records, skill validations, credential expiration tracking, renewal requirements, and compliance with industry-specific certification mandates. Supports credentialing requirements for healthcare, IT, skilled trades, finance, government, and other specialized staffing verticals.' .

ind:Vendor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for all third-party staffing supplier, subcontractor, and service provider data within MSP and VMS-managed programs. Owns vendor profiles, tier classifications, rate cards, rate agreements, Beeline VMS program enrollment, SOW vendor agreements, IC (Independent Contractor) supplier records, vendor performance scorecards, vendor contracts, and vendor compliance tracking. Supports multi-vendor contingent workforce programs and managed service provider operations.' .

ind:Contract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all commercial agreement and contract lifecycle data. Covers Master Service Agreements (MSA) terms, Statements of Work (SOW) execution, rate schedule amendments, non-disclosure agreements (NDA), non-compete clauses, service level agreements (SLA), contract amendments, renewal and expiration tracking, and e-signature workflows via DocuSign CLM. SSOT for the legal and commercial terms governing all client and vendor contractual commitments.' .

ind:Onboarding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Onboarding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns the end-to-end worker onboarding and offboarding process data. Covers onboarding task checklists, document collection (I-9, direct deposit, tax forms), orientation completion, LMS (Learning Management System) training assignments via SAP SuccessFactors, equipment provisioning, assignment-end workflows, and offboarding processes. Bridges credentialing, compliance, and placement domains to ensure workers are fully ready for assignment start.' .

ind:Finance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all financial accounting, accounts receivable, accounts payable, general ledger, revenue recognition, and financial reporting data for the staffing enterprise' .

ind:Employee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Employee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns internal employee (recruiter, account manager, operations staff) identity, role, team structure, compensation, and performance data. Distinct from candidate (external talent supply) and placement (worker assignments)' .

ind:Shared rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:StaffingHr ;
    rdfs:label 'Shared' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Shared domain (auto-created for table holiday_calendar)' .

# --- Data Product Classes (Tables) ---
ind:Timesheet rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Timesheet' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record for a worker\'s timesheet submission covering a defined pay period. Represents the authoritative timesheet header sourced from Kronos Workforce Ready, capturing the worker, assignment, client, pay period dates, submission status, total regular hours, OT hours, DT hours, per diem, approval state, and audit timestamps. This is the SSOT for all billable and payable hours for a given worker-assignment-period combination. Subject to FLSA §516 recordkeeping requirements (minimum 3-year retention of hours worked, wages paid, and conditions of employment). Supports state-specific meal/rest break compliance tracking for California, Washington, Oregon, and other jurisdictions with mandatory break laws.' .

ind:TimeEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Time Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular daily or shift-level time record representing a single worked period for a contingent worker. This is the unified SSOT for all shift-level and daily worked-time data — there is no separate shift product. Captures the specific date, planned and actual start/end times, break duration, meal break compliance flag, rest break compliance flag, net hours worked, pay type (regular, OT, DT), shift differential code, shift type (day/evening/night/weekend), labor category, cost center, schedule variance (planned vs actual hours delta), and entry source (Kronos clock, mobile, manual). Child record of the timesheet header. Incorporates shift-level schedule comparison, shift differential tracking, and dispatch-relevant shift metadata. Feeds both payroll and billing calculations. Links raw punch events to the timesheet summary. Subject to FLSA §516 and state-specific recordkeeping requirements including California Labor Code §226 (itemized wage statement backing data).' .

ind:TimesheetApprovalWorkflow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Timesheet Approval Workflow' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the multi-step approval workflow lifecycle for a timesheet submission. Captures each approval stage (worker submission, supervisor review, client approval, back-office audit), the approver identity, approval action (approved, rejected, escalated, auto-approved), action timestamp, rejection reason, and SLA compliance flag. Enables full audit trail of who approved what and when, supporting dispute resolution and compliance requirements.' .

ind:AbsenceRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Absence Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records worker absences, PTO usage, sick leave, FMLA leave, holiday observances, jury duty, bereavement, and unexcused absences within a pay period. Captures absence type, absence date range, hours absent, PTO balance consumed, leave reason code, approval status, paid/unpaid indicator, client notification flag, and replacement worker request trigger. Sourced from Kronos Workforce Ready leave management module. Feeds payroll deductions, workforce availability reporting, and client SLA compliance tracking. For contingent workers, unexcused absences may trigger assignment termination workflows. Subject to FMLA recordkeeping requirements (3-year retention) and state-specific paid sick leave laws (e.g., California Healthy Workplaces, Healthy Families Act).' .

ind:Schedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the planned work schedule for a contingent worker on a specific assignment, including scheduled shift start/end times, days of week, shift type (day/evening/night/weekend), expected weekly hours, and effective date range. Sourced from Kronos Workforce Ready scheduling module. Serves as the baseline against which actual time entries are compared for variance analysis and OT calculation.' .

ind:Shift rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Shift' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents a specific scheduled or worked shift instance for a worker, capturing the shift date, planned start/end, actual start/end, shift duration, break time, net hours, shift differential code, and variance from schedule. Distinct from time_entry in that it represents the shift-level aggregation and schedule comparison, while time_entry captures individual punches. Supports scheduling dispatch and labor analytics.' .

ind:OtRule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Ot Rule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference entity defining overtime and double-time calculation rules applicable to specific clients, states, job categories, or worker classifications. Captures the weekly OT threshold (e.g., 40 hrs/week federal FLSA §207), daily OT threshold (e.g., 8 hrs/day California Labor Code §510), DT threshold (e.g., 12 hrs/day California), seventh-consecutive-day rules, applicable FLSA exemption status, state-specific OT law references, effective date range, and rule priority for conflict resolution. Supports blended OT rate calculation for workers on multiple assignments. Includes prevailing wage OT rules for Davis-Bacon Act compliance on government staffing contracts. Ensures compliant OT/DT classification across all time entries in multi-state staffing operations.' .

ind:PayPeriod rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Period' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference entity defining pay period cycles used across the staffing operation. Captures pay period type (weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly), period start date, period end date, payroll processing cutoff date, check date, fiscal week number, holiday adjustment flag, and active status. Serves as the authoritative calendar for timesheet grouping, payroll runs, and billing cycle alignment. Critical for multi-state operations where different clients may operate on different pay cycles.' .

ind:ApprovedHoursSummary rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Hours Summary' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified aggregated summary of approved hours for a worker-assignment-client combination within a pay period, broken down by pay type (regular, OT, DT, per diem, holiday). Serves as the single authoritative handoff record for both client invoice generation (billing domain) and payroll processing (payroll domain). Captures total regular hours, OT hours, DT hours, per diem units, bill rate applied, pay rate applied, total billable amount, total payable amount, burden rate components, approval confirmation flag, and payroll transmission status. Replaces separate billable and payable hour summaries to ensure a single reconciled SSOT. Distinct from raw time_entry records — this is the approved, billing-and-payroll-ready output of the timesheet approval process.' .

ind:PerDiemClaim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Per Diem Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records per diem allowance claims submitted by contingent workers for travel, lodging, and meal reimbursements associated with a specific assignment. Captures claim date, per diem type (travel, lodging, meals, incidentals), claimed amount, approved amount, expense location, receipt indicator, approval status, and IRS per diem rate reference. Feeds both payroll (non-taxable reimbursements) and billing (client-billable per diem charges).' .

ind:Adjustment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Adjustment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records post-submission corrections and amendments to approved timesheets, capturing the original timesheet reference, adjustment type (hours correction, rate correction, pay type reclassification, retroactive change), original values, adjusted values, adjustment reason, requestor, approver, and effective pay period. Maintains a complete audit trail of all timesheet modifications for compliance, dispute resolution, and payroll/billing reconciliation.' .

ind:PunchEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Punch Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Raw, immutable clock event record capturing individual worker punch-in and punch-out events from Kronos Workforce Ready time clocks, mobile apps, or web portals. Stores the exact UTC timestamp, punch type (in/out/break-start/break-end/transfer), device ID, location coordinates, geofence validation result, biometric verification flag, IP address, and raw source payload. Multiple punch events are processed into a single time_entry record. Serves as the tamper-proof audit-grade source record for FLSA compliance, wage-and-hour dispute resolution, and DOL audit defense. Retention policy: minimum 3 years per FLSA recordkeeping requirements.' .

ind:LaborCategory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Labor Category' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference entity defining labor categories and work classifications used to categorize time entries for cost allocation, billing rate determination, and workforce analytics. Captures category code, category name, skill level, FLSA classification (exempt/non-exempt), prevailing wage indicator, prevailing wage rate (for Davis-Bacon Act compliance on government staffing contracts), union code applicability, SCA (Service Contract Act) labor category mapping, and default bill/pay rate tier. Used by clients and staffing operations to segment labor costs by function, skill, or contract type. Links to ot_rule for determining applicable overtime calculation rules.' .

ind:TimesheetDispute rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Timesheet Dispute' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks formal disputes raised by workers or clients against submitted or approved timesheets. Captures dispute type (hours discrepancy, rate dispute, missing time, unauthorized OT), dispute initiator (worker, client, back-office), disputed timesheet reference, disputed amount, dispute status (open, under review, resolved, escalated), resolution outcome, resolution date, and responsible party. Supports SLA tracking for dispute resolution and feeds compliance reporting.' .

ind:VmsTimesheetSync rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Timesheet ;
    rdfs:label 'Vms Timesheet Sync' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the bidirectional synchronization and reconciliation of timesheet records between the internal Kronos Workforce Ready system and client Vendor Management System (VMS) platforms such as Beeline, Fieldglass, VNDLY, or Coupa. Captures the VMS platform identifier, VMS timesheet reference ID, sync direction (push/pull), sync status (pending, synced, failed, rejected, partial), sync timestamp, error codes, field-level mapping discrepancies, retry count, manual override flags, and reconciliation outcome. Critical for MSP/VMS-managed programs where client approval occurs within the VMS portal and hours must match exactly between systems to avoid billing disputes.' .

ind:ClientAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Client Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for every client (employer) organization that Staffing Hr serves. SSOT for client company identity, classification, and billing configuration. Sourced from Bullhorn ATS/CRM and Salesforce Revenue Cloud. Captures legal entity name, DBA name, DUNS number, FEIN, industry classification (NAICS/SIC), company size tier, client type (direct, VMS/MSP, RPO), account status (prospect, active, inactive, on-hold, terminated), primary business address, website, and CRM account owner. Also owns billing preferences: invoice delivery method, invoice frequency, invoice grouping rules (by location, department, cost center, or consolidated), PO number requirements, payment method (ACH, check, wire), billing contact, and preferred payment portal. Demand-side anchor entity for all job orders, placements, billing, and commercial relationships.' .

ind:ClientContact rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Client Contact' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual person record at a client organization who interacts with Staffing Hr in a business capacity. Sourced from Bullhorn CRM and Salesforce. Captures full name, job title, department, direct phone, mobile, business email, contact type (hiring manager, procurement, AP, executive sponsor, VMS coordinator), preferred communication channel, LinkedIn URL, contact status, and opt-in/opt-out flags. Supports CRM engagement tracking and relationship management workflows.' .

ind:AccountHierarchy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Account Hierarchy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Parent-child organizational relationship between client accounts, enabling enterprise account structures such as global parent, regional subsidiary, and local site. Captures parent account reference, child account reference, hierarchy level, relationship type (corporate parent, division, subsidiary, franchise), effective date, and end date. Critical for consolidated billing, enterprise SLA management, MSP/VMS program roll-ups, and territory planning across account families.' .

ind:Location rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical or virtual work site associated with a client account. Represents the specific facility, office, plant, or remote work designation where workers are deployed. Captures site name, address (street, city, state, zip, country), location type (headquarters, branch, warehouse, remote, on-site), OSHA establishment ID, workers comp jurisdiction state, site contact, parking/badge instructions, and active status. Used for assignment dispatch, workers comp classification, and compliance jurisdiction mapping.' .

ind:ClientRateCard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Client Rate Card' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Negotiated bill rate and markup schedule agreed upon with a client under an MSA or VMS program agreement. Captures job category, job title, skill level, bill rate (regular, OT, DT), pay rate guidance, markup percentage, spread (bill minus pay), burden rate inclusion flag, per diem rate, currency, effective date, expiration date, rate card version, and approval status. Sourced from Beeline VMS and Salesforce Revenue Cloud. Serves as the client-domain pricing reference for job order creation, candidate submittal pricing, and invoice generation. Note: contract-level rate schedule terms, rate escalation clauses, and contractual rate governance are owned by the contract domain; this product owns the operational rate table used in day-to-day staffing transactions.' .

ind:VmsProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Vms Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor Management System program record representing a client-managed contingent workforce program administered through a VMS technology platform. Captures program name, VMS platform (Beeline, Fieldglass, Coupa, IQNavigator), MSP partner name (if applicable), program type (MSP-managed, self-managed, hybrid), program scope (all categories, IT only, light industrial, professional, etc.), supplier tier structure, requisition routing rules, markup cap, program start date, program end date, and program status. Sourced from Beeline VMS integration. Critical for staffing firms participating in managed programs where requisition flow, rate caps, and supplier tiering are controlled by the client or their MSP.' .

ind:ClientEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Client Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'CRM engagement activity record capturing all touchpoints and interactions between Staffing Hr staff and client contacts. Sourced from Bullhorn CRM and Salesforce. Captures engagement type (call, email, meeting, site visit, QBR, proposal presentation, NPS survey), engagement date and time, duration, subject, outcome, next action, assigned recruiter or account manager, and engagement channel. Supports relationship health monitoring, account management cadence tracking, and pipeline development.' .

ind:NpsResponse rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Nps Response' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Net Promoter Score survey response record capturing client satisfaction feedback at a point in time. Captures survey date, respondent contact, NPS score (0-10), promoter/passive/detractor classification, verbatim comment, survey channel (email, phone, in-app), survey trigger (quarterly, post-placement, post-fill), follow-up required flag, follow-up owner, and resolution status. Enables client satisfaction trending, account health scoring inputs, and retention risk identification.' .

ind:AccountSegment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Account Segment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial segmentation and classification record for a client account, defining strategic tier, revenue potential, and service model. Captures segment tier (strategic, key, growth, transactional), vertical industry focus, geographic market, annual revenue band, headcount band, estimated annual staffing spend, wallet share estimate, primary service line (temp staffing, direct hire, RPO, MSP), account manager assignment, and segment review date. Used for territory planning, resource allocation, and go-to-market prioritization.' .

ind:ProgramSupplier rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Supplier' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association record linking a staffing supplier (vendor) to a specific VMS program, capturing the supplier\'s participation terms and performance within a client-managed contingent workforce program. Captures supplier tier (preferred, approved, backup), category authorization (which job categories the supplier can fill), markup cap for this supplier within the program, submission limit per requisition, performance score, program enrollment date, certification/compliance status within the program, and supplier status (active, suspended, removed). Sourced from Beeline VMS. Note: supplier/vendor identity and master data are owned by the vendor domain; this product owns only the program-specific participation terms, tier assignments, and performance metrics within the client\'s program context.' .

ind:SlaMeasurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Measurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic performance measurement record capturing actual results against a defined SLA configuration for a specific reporting window. Captures measurement period (start/end date), SLA config reference, measured value, target value, variance, compliance flag (met/missed), requisition count in scope, fill count, TTF (Time to Fill) actual average, TTS (Time to Start) actual average, QoS (Quality of Submission) actual rate, fill rate actual, and measurement source system. Generated from operational data in the recruitment and placement domains. Enables SLA compliance reporting, client QBR (Quarterly Business Review) preparation, penalty/bonus calculation triggers, and account health scoring.' .

ind:I9Verification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'I9 Verification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for I-9 Employment Eligibility Verification for each worker. Tracks Section 1 (employee attestation), Section 2 (employer document review), Section 3 (reverification/rehire), document types presented, document numbers, expiration dates, E-Verify case number linkage, completion status, and re-verification due dates. SSOT for I-9 compliance per INA requirements. Sourced from onboarding workflows and Sterling BGC system.' .

ind:EverifyCase rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Everify Case' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each E-Verify case submitted to DHS/SSA for worker employment eligibility confirmation. Captures case number, submission timestamp, initial case result (Employment Authorized, Tentative Nonconfirmation - TNC, Final Nonconfirmation), TNC resolution status, referral dates, closure reason, and federal case closure code. Links to i9_verification. Sourced from Sterling BGC and E-Verify federal portal integration.' .

ind:WorkerClassification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Worker Classification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record capturing FLSA worker classification determinations for each worker engagement — W-2 employee vs. 1099 independent contractor (IC). Stores classification type, determination basis (behavioral control, financial control, relationship type per IRS common law test), classification date, reviewing attorney or compliance officer, client-requested classification, override flags, co-employment risk rating, and IRS audit exposure notes. SSOT for IC vs. W-2 classification decisions.' .

ind:EeocFiling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Eeoc Filing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for EEOC (Equal Employment Opportunity Commission) regulatory filings and reports submitted on behalf of the staffing firm or client. Covers EEO-1 Component 1 report submissions, filing period, establishment count, total headcount by race/ethnicity/gender/job category, submission confirmation number, filing status, and amendment history. Supports EEOC and OFCCP audit readiness.' .

ind:OfccpCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ofccp Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for OFCCP (Office of Federal Contract Compliance Programs) compliance management, including both Affirmative Action Plans (AAP) and OFCCP audits/desk reviews. AAP data captures plan year, establishment covered, workforce analysis, availability analysis, utilization analysis, placement goals by job group, good-faith effort documentation, plan approval date, and plan custodian. Audit data tracks audit type (Compliance Review, Focused Review, Complaint Investigation), audit initiation date, OFCCP district office, conciliation agreement status, corrective action plan, resolution date, and monetary relief amounts. Required for federal contractor compliance under Executive Order 11246 and supports annual AAP certification and OFCCP audit response.' .

ind:OshaIncident rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Osha Incident' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for OSHA recordable workplace safety incidents involving contingent workers on client sites. Captures incident date, client site location, injury/illness type, body part affected, OSHA recordability determination (recordable vs. first-aid only), days away from work, restricted duty days, OSHA 300 log entry number, workers compensation claim linkage, root cause, and corrective action taken. Supports OSHA 300/300A annual summary reporting.' .

ind:CoeRiskAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Coe Risk Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for co-employment (Co-E) and joint employment risk assessments conducted for client engagements. Captures assessment date, client account, engagement type (temp, contract, SOW, managed service, RPO), risk factors evaluated (supervision level, equipment provision, integration into client workforce, assignment duration, client control over work methods, disciplinary authority, pay rate setting), risk rating (low/medium/high/critical), recommended mitigation actions (contract language, worker communication protocols, supervisor training, co-employment insurance rider), legal counsel review status, and reassessment schedule. SSOT for co-employment liability management per DOL joint employer standards, NLRB Browning-Ferris framework, and state-specific joint employer tests. Critical for staffing firms where co-employment is the #1 structural legal risk.' .

ind:RegulatoryViolation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Violation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for identified regulatory violations, compliance breaches, and enforcement actions across all regulatory frameworks (DOL, EEOC, OSHA, IRS, FCRA, GDPR, CCPA, state labor boards). Captures violation type, regulatory body, applicable regulation/statute, discovery date, discovery method (internal audit, external complaint, agency notice, whistleblower report, client notification, self-assessment), severity level (minor/moderate/major/critical), affected worker or client count, root cause category, remediation plan, remediation owner, remediation due date, resolution status, financial penalty amount, legal counsel involvement flag, and board notification flag. SSOT for compliance incident tracking. Supports compliance dashboard KPIs, regulatory risk trending, and board-level compliance reporting.' .

ind:Audit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for internal and external compliance audits conducted across the staffing firm\'s operations, with embedded audit finding detail records. Covers audit type (I-9 audit, payroll tax audit, FLSA audit, FCRA audit, SOC 2 audit, client compliance audit, DOL audit), audit scope, auditor (internal team or external firm), audit period, and final audit disposition. Each audit contains one-to-many finding records capturing: finding category (documentation gap, process failure, regulatory breach, control weakness), regulatory citation, affected population size, risk rating (low/medium/high/critical), recommended corrective action, responsible owner, due date, remediation evidence, and closure status. SSOT for all compliance audit activity and finding lifecycle management from identification through closure. Distinct from ofccp_compliance which covers OFCCP-specific federal contractor reviews and Affirmative Action Plans.' .

ind:PrivacyRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Privacy Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for data subject rights requests received under GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable privacy regulations. Captures request type (access, deletion, portability, opt-out of sale, correction), requestor identity, submission channel, submission date, regulatory deadline (30/45/60 days), fulfillment status, data categories involved, response date, and exemption flags. Supports GDPR Article 15-22 and CCPA Section 1798.100+ compliance.' .

ind:WageHourDetermination rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Wage Hour Determination' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for wage and hour compliance determinations made for worker engagements, covering FLSA overtime eligibility, state-specific minimum wage applicability, prevailing wage determinations (Davis-Bacon, Service Contract Act), exempt vs. non-exempt classification, and pay equity assessments. Captures determination date, applicable law/regulation, pay rate validated, overtime threshold, and compliance officer sign-off. Supports DOL audit readiness and FLSA litigation defense.' .

ind:Requirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for federal regulations and client-specific contractual compliance requirements that govern staffing operations. Each record defines a requirement type (federal regulation, client contractual mandate, industry standard), applicable jurisdiction scope, effective date, expiration date, governing body, requirement description, and mandatory documentation checklist. Serves as the compliance rule catalog driving requirement-to-worker and requirement-to-placement enforcement checks. Distinct from state_compliance_rule which owns state-specific and local jurisdiction requirements that vary by geography.' .

ind:PlacementComplianceCheck rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Placement Compliance Check' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the compliance gate-check results for each worker placement prior to assignment start or extension. Validates that all applicable federal, state, and client-specific compliance requirements are satisfied: I-9 complete, E-Verify authorized, BGC cleared, drug screen passed, required credentials verified, safety training complete, worker classification determined, co-employment risk assessed, wage and hour determination completed, and client-specific requirements met. Each check item has a pass/fail/waived/pending status, check date, reviewer, and waiver authorization (if applicable). Acts as the compliance clearance record before a placement goes active. Supports real-time compliance dashboards and prevents non-compliant placements from generating billable hours.' .

ind:WorkersCompPolicy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Workers Comp Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for workers\' compensation insurance policies and associated claims covering contingent workers across states. Policy header captures policy number, insurance carrier, policy period, covered states, experience modification rate (EMR), NCCI class codes by job type, premium amounts, and policy renewal dates. Claim detail records capture claim number, incident date, filing date, injury description, claim type (medical only, lost time, permanent partial disability), claim status (open, reserved, closed, reopened), total incurred cost, reserve amount, adjuster, litigation flag, subrogation flag, and settlement date. Links to osha_incident for workplace injury correlation. SSOT for all workers\' compensation policy and claim data. Managed through TempWorks Payroll integration. Supports OSHA incident linkage, state-mandated workers\' comp compliance, experience mod management, and insurance cost optimization.' .

ind:Assignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record for every temporary, contract, contract-to-hire, and temp-to-perm worker assignment. Serves as the SSOT for active worker assignment status, connecting a candidate to a job order at a specific client work location. Tracks assignment type (temp, CTH, temp-to-perm), start date, scheduled end date, actual end date, assignment status (active, ended, extended, converted, cancelled), supervisor name, work location, bill rate, pay rate, spread, markup percentage, FLSA classification, workers comp code, cost center, PO number, and redeployment eligibility flag. Primary operational entity of the placement domain and the backbone of the Bullhorn ATS placement record.' .

ind:DirectHire rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Direct Hire' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for permanent placement and direct hire engagements where a candidate is placed full-time with a client. Distinct from temporary assignment lifecycle — tracks offer date, accepted date, start date, base salary, conversion fee amount, fee percentage, fee payment terms, guarantee period (fall-off window), fall-off date if applicable, replacement obligation flag, and placement status (offered, accepted, started, fell-off, replaced). Owned by the placement domain as the SSOT for permanent placement outcomes. Sourced from Bullhorn permanent placement module.' .

ind:AssignmentExtension rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment Extension' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each extension event on a temporary or contract assignment. Tracks the prior end date, new end date, extension reason, extension request date, approver, revised bill rate (if renegotiated), revised pay rate, extension sequence number, and extension status (pending, approved, rejected, executed). Enables fall-off rate monitoring and redeployment planning by providing a complete extension history per assignment. Sourced from Bullhorn assignment extension workflow.' .

ind:Conversion rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Conversion' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the temp-to-perm or contract-to-hire conversion event when a temporary worker transitions to a permanent employee of the client. Tracks conversion date, conversion type (temp-to-perm, CTH), original assignment reference, conversion fee amount, fee waiver flag, fee waiver reason, conversion notice date, client confirmation date, and conversion status (pending, confirmed, invoiced, fell-off). Critical for billing the conversion fee and monitoring conversion rate KPIs. Sourced from Bullhorn placement conversion workflow.' .

ind:AssignmentStatusHistory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment Status History' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Audit trail of all status transitions for a worker assignment throughout its lifecycle (e.g., offered → confirmed → active → extended → ended, or active → cancelled). Captures prior status, new status, transition timestamp, changed-by user, change reason code, and any associated notes. Enables SLA compliance tracking (TTF, TTS), fall-off rate analysis, and regulatory audit requirements. Supports Bullhorn status change event log.' .

ind:Redeployment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Redeployment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks redeployment events and pipeline management for workers coming off active assignments (bench management). Records the ending assignment reference, redeployment target date, redeployment status (bench, in-process, redeployed, separated), candidate availability date, preferred work type, preferred location, redeployment coordinator, days on bench, and outcome (redeployed to new assignment, converted, separated). Enables proactive bench management and reduces time-to-redeploy KPI. Sourced from Bullhorn redeployment workflow.' .

ind:Backfill rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Backfill' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking backfill requests and fulfillment when a placed worker must be replaced on an active assignment due to early termination, no-show, client request, or injury. Records original assignment reference, backfill trigger reason, backfill request date, required fill date, backfill status (open, filled, cancelled), replacement assignment reference, and days-to-backfill metric. Drives client SLA compliance, fall-off rate monitoring, and recruiter workload prioritization. Sourced from Bullhorn assignment backfill workflow.' .

ind:Rate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all negotiated rate components associated with a specific assignment or direct hire placement. Each rate record represents a single rate type — standard bill/pay rate, overtime (OT), double-time (DT), holiday, per diem (travel, lodging, meals, incidentals), or burden rate. Tracks effective date, expiration date, rate type, bill rate amount, pay rate amount, spread amount, markup percentage, gross margin percentage, burden rate, workers comp rate, IRS GSA rate reference (for per diem), taxable flag, reimbursement method, per diem daily allowance, per diem budget cap, rate approval status, and rate card source. Serves as the SSOT for all placement-level rate and per diem data feeding payroll and billing domains. Per diem rate types include travel, lodging, meals, and incidentals with IRS GSA compliance tracking. Sourced from Bullhorn rate card, Beeline VMS rate management, and TempWorks Payroll per diem configuration.' .

ind:WorkLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for physical or virtual work locations where placed workers perform their assignments, including dispatch and scheduling locations. Tracks location name, address, client site details, remote/hybrid designation, and capacity planning attributes.' .

ind:Supervisor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Supervisor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the client-side supervisor or hiring manager who directly oversees placed workers at a work location. Tracks supervisor full name, title, email, phone, client company reference, work location reference, supervisor type (direct manager, site supervisor, project lead), timesheet approval authority flag, onboarding contact flag, and active status. This is the operational assignment supervision relationship — distinct from the client contact master in the client domain. Used for timesheet routing, performance escalation, day-one onboarding coordination, and assignment check-in scheduling. Sourced from Bullhorn contact and assignment supervisor fields.' .

ind:FallOff rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Fall Off' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing fall-off events where a placed candidate leaves or is removed from an assignment or direct hire within the guarantee period. Tracks fall-off date, fall-off reason code (candidate quit, client termination, no-show, performance, personal), days-to-fall-off, guarantee period days, replacement obligation flag, replacement deadline, replacement status, revenue impact amount, and recruiter accountability reference. Critical for fall-off rate KPI monitoring and client SLA compliance. Sourced from Bullhorn placement fall-off workflow.' .

ind:SowEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Sow Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Statement of Work (SOW) based placements where workers are engaged under a defined deliverable-based contract rather than a time-and-materials assignment. Tracks SOW reference number, SOW title, engagement start date, engagement end date, total SOW value, milestone-based billing flag, deliverable descriptions, SOW status (draft, active, completed, terminated), IC classification flag, co-employment risk assessment, and vendor reference for MSP-managed SOW programs. Distinct from the contract domain\'s SOW template — this product tracks the operational placement-level engagement instance, not the commercial agreement terms. Sourced from DocuSign CLM and Beeline VMS SOW module.' .

ind:PerDiem rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Per Diem' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for per diem allowance arrangements associated with a specific assignment, covering travel, lodging, and meal reimbursements for workers placed at remote or out-of-area work locations. Tracks per diem type (travel, lodging, meals, incidentals), daily rate, IRS GSA rate reference, effective date, expiration date, taxable flag, reimbursement method (payroll-included, separate expense), approval status, and total per diem budget for the assignment. Sourced from TempWorks Payroll per diem configuration and Bullhorn assignment details.' .

ind:Offer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Offer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the formal job offer extended to a candidate for a temporary assignment, contract-to-hire, or permanent placement. Tracks offer date, offer type (temp, CTH, perm, SOW), offered bill rate, offered pay rate, offered salary, sign-on bonus, offer expiration date, offer status (pending, accepted, declined, rescinded, expired, counter-offered), decline reason code, counter-offer details, negotiation round count, and offer-to-acceptance cycle time. Serves as the bridge between the recruitment submittal process and the active assignment or direct hire record. Critical for offer acceptance rate KPI, time-to-fill analytics, and compensation benchmarking. Sourced from Bullhorn offer management workflow.' .

ind:Supplier rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all third-party staffing suppliers, subcontractors, independent contractor (IC) suppliers, and service providers participating in MSP/VMS-managed contingent workforce programs. Captures vendor identity, legal entity details, business type (staffing agency, IC supplier, SOW provider, subcontractor), tax classification (W-2, 1099, Corp-to-Corp), EIN, DUNS number, NAICS code, diversity certifications (MBE, WBE, SDVOB), primary contact, headquarters address, operational regions, onboarding status, and Beeline VMS enrollment status. For IC supplier subtypes, additionally captures IRS worker classification determination, IC compliance program enrollment status, IC compliance vendor (e.g., MBO Partners, Shiftpixy), indemnification agreement status, right-to-audit clause, insurance minimums, IC risk score, and business structure (sole prop, LLC, S-Corp, C-Corp). SSOT for ALL vendor identity across all programs — all vendor types including staffing agencies, IC suppliers, SOW providers, and subcontractors are unified in this single master record. The ic_supplier subtype is distinguished by business_type and carries additional IC-specific compliance attributes within this same entity to avoid data divergence across staffing agency and IC supplier workflows.' .

ind:TierClassification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Tier Classification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference and history table defining vendor tier levels and tracking tier reclassification events within MSP/VMS programs. Tier definitions capture tier code, tier name (e.g., Tier 1 Preferred, Tier 2 Approved, Tier 3 Conditional, Tier 4 Probationary), tier description, program eligibility rules, submission priority order, maximum fill-rate allocation percentage, SLA requirements per tier, and review cycle frequency. Tier review history captures review date, vendor ID, previous tier, proposed tier, review trigger (scheduled, performance-based, compliance failure, client request), scorecard period referenced, review committee members, decision outcome (upgraded, downgraded, maintained, suspended), effective date of tier change, rationale notes, and approval status. Drives vendor routing logic in Beeline VMS and provides full audit trail for tier movement decisions.' .

ind:VmsEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Vms Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks each vendor\'s enrollment, participation record, and onboarding task completion within the Beeline VMS contingent workforce program. Captures enrollment date, program name, client program ID, enrollment status (active, suspended, terminated, pending), approved job categories, approved work locations, VMS portal credentials status, electronic onboarding completion flag, MSP sponsor, enrollment agreement reference, and vendor onboarding workflow tasks (document submission, insurance verification, system access provisioning, training completion, contract execution, compliance attestation) with task status, due dates, completion dates, assigned reviewers, and blocking flags. One record per vendor per VMS program. Supports multi-client MSP program management and tracks the full supplier-organization-level onboarding lifecycle from initial enrollment through full program activation. Distinct from worker onboarding (owned by the onboarding domain) — this is supplier-organization-level enrollment and onboarding.' .

ind:VendorRateCard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Rate Card' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the standard bill rate and pay rate schedule negotiated with a vendor for specific job categories, skill levels, and labor classifications within a VMS program or MSP engagement. Captures vendor ID, job category, labor category (e.g., IT, light industrial, clerical, professional), skill level (e.g., junior, mid, senior, lead), standard bill rate, standard pay rate, OT bill rate, OT pay rate, DT bill rate, DT pay rate, per diem rate, currency, effective date, expiration date, geographic market, and rate card version. Serves as the rate template from which binding rate_agreement records are executed. Supports rate benchmarking, spread analysis, and market rate comparison across the vendor supply chain.' .

ind:RateAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Rate Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the formally executed rate agreement between the MSP/staffing firm and a vendor supplier for a specific client program or engagement period. Tracks agreement reference number, vendor ID, client program, negotiated markup percentage, spread floor, rate lock period, rate escalation clauses, approved rate exceptions, signatory names, execution date, effective start date, expiration date, and DocuSign CLM document reference. Distinct from the rate card template — this is the binding executed agreement.' .

ind:SowAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Sow Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages Statement of Work (SOW) agreements executed with vendors for project-based or deliverable-based engagements within the vendor program. Captures SOW number, vendor ID, client ID, project title, scope of work description, deliverables list, fixed price or T&M structure, total contract value, milestone schedule, start date, end date, amendment history, SOW status (draft, executed, active, closed, terminated), DocuSign CLM reference, and co-employment risk classification. Supports SOW vendor program management distinct from staff augmentation. Note: This product owns the vendor-side SOW relationship and program enrollment aspects; the contract domain owns the commercial contract lifecycle and legal terms of the SOW.' .

ind:PerformanceScorecard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Scorecard' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic vendor performance scorecard capturing quantitative and qualitative KPIs for each supplier within an MSP/VMS program. Tracks evaluation period, overall score, TTF (Time to Fill) score, QoS (Quality of Submission) score, submittal-to-interview ratio, interview-to-offer ratio, offer-to-start ratio, fall-off rate, assignment completion rate, compliance rate, NPS score, client satisfaction rating, redeployment rate, and scorecard status (draft, published, disputed, finalized). Drives tier reclassification and program allocation decisions.' .

ind:VendorContact rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Contact' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for individual contacts associated with a vendor/supplier organization. Captures contact full name, job title, role type (account manager, recruiter, compliance officer, billing contact, executive sponsor), email, phone, mobile, preferred communication method, contact status (active, inactive), primary contact flag, and the vendor organization they represent. Supports relationship management and communication routing for MSP program operations.' .

ind:ProgramAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the requisition fill-rate allocation and submission quota assigned to each vendor within a specific client VMS program and job category. Captures program ID, vendor ID, job category, tier classification reference, allocation percentage, maximum concurrent submissions allowed, priority rank within tier, allocation effective date, expiration date, and allocation status (active, suspended, exhausted). Governs how job orders are distributed across the vendor supply chain in Beeline VMS to ensure preferred suppliers receive first-look access per MSP program rules. Updated periodically based on scorecard results and tier reclassification decisions.' .

ind:VendorCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks vendor-level compliance status, regulatory obligation fulfillment, and insurance certificate records for each supplier in the MSP/VMS program. Captures compliance category (insurance, E-Verify, EEOC, OFCCP, OSHA, FCRA, I-9 audit, workers comp, FUTA/SUTA registration, non-compete policy, data security SOC 2), compliance item description, required document, document expiration date, compliance status (compliant, non-compliant, pending review, waived), last audit date, next review date, remediation notes, and compliance officer assigned. For insurance-category records, additionally captures certificate number, insurance type (general liability, professional liability/E&O, workers compensation, cyber liability, umbrella), carrier name, policy number, coverage limit, certificate holder (MSP/client), additional insured status, auto-renewal flag, and COI document reference. Triggers compliance alerts when documents or certificates approach expiration. Distinct from the credentialing domain which tracks worker-level credentials.' .

ind:PreferredSupplierList rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Preferred Supplier List' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages the Preferred Supplier List (PSL) — the curated, approved roster of vendors authorized to supply contingent workers or SOW services for a specific client program or job category. Captures client program ID, vendor ID, job category, PSL status (preferred, approved, conditional, excluded), inclusion date, exclusion date, PSL version, approval authority, and client-specific notes. Governs which vendors are visible and eligible to receive requisitions in the VMS for each client engagement.' .

ind:DiversityCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Diversity Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks vendor diversity certifications required for OFCCP compliance, client diversity spend reporting, and supplier diversity program participation. Captures certification type (MBE, WBE, SDVOB, HUBZone, 8(a), LGBTBE, VOSB), certifying body (NMSDC, WBENC, SBA, USVBA), certification number, issue date, expiration date, certification status (active, expired, pending renewal, revoked), and supporting document reference. Enables diversity spend analytics and OFCCP supplier diversity reporting.' .

ind:Exclusion rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Exclusion' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Maintains the vendor exclusion and debarment registry — suppliers that are prohibited from participating in specific client programs, job categories, or the entire MSP program due to compliance failures, performance issues, legal disputes, client blacklisting, or regulatory debarment (SAM.gov, OFAC, OIG). Captures vendor ID, exclusion scope (program-level, client-level, global), exclusion reason category, exclusion narrative, exclusion effective date, exclusion authority (MSP program manager, client, regulatory body), reinstatement eligibility flag, reinstatement conditions, reinstatement date if applicable, appeal status, and supporting documentation reference. Critical for risk management — the VMS must check this registry before routing any requisition to prevent excluded vendors from receiving job orders. Feeds into preferred_supplier_list eligibility and program_allocation enforcement.' .

ind:Profile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT master record for every talent supply-side individual tracked in the ATS. Stores core identity: legal name, preferred name, date of birth, gender, pronouns, contact details (email, phone, address), SSN (masked), LinkedIn URL, portfolio URL, candidate type (W-2, 1099, EOR), current employment status, ATS record ID, source system, data classification level, GDPR/CCPA consent flags, do-not-contact flag, and audit timestamps. Captures sourcing attribution: source channel type (job board, referral, social media, direct outreach, RPO campaign, VMS portal, career site, walk-in), source channel name, campaign ID, sourcing recruiter, sourcing date, cost-per-source, UTM parameters, and attribution model (first-touch, last-touch, multi-touch). Anchor entity for the entire candidate domain — all child entities resolve to this record via profile_id FK.' .

ind:Resume rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Resume' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores parsed and raw resume content for each candidate version. Tracks resume version number, file format (PDF, DOCX), raw text blob, parsed structured content (skills extracted, titles extracted, education extracted), parsing engine used (e.g., Sovren, Textkernel), parse confidence score, upload source (portal, recruiter upload, email parse), upload timestamp, active version flag, and storage URI. Supports ATS resume search and talent pool matching workflows in Bullhorn.' .

ind:WorkHistory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Work History' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Structured employment history records for each candidate, capturing prior employer name, job title held, employment type (FTE, contract, temp, self-employed), start date, end date, is_current flag, industry sector, responsibilities summary, reason for leaving, verified flag, verification source, and gap indicator. Sourced from resume parsing and candidate-submitted data in Bullhorn. Used for tenure analysis, skill inference, and placement suitability scoring.' .

ind:Skill rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Skill' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Canonical skill inventory record for a candidate, representing a single skill or competency attributed to the individual. Captures skill name (normalized to a controlled taxonomy where available), skill category (technical, soft skill, domain expertise, language, tool/platform), proficiency level (beginner, intermediate, advanced, expert), years of experience with the skill, last used date, skill source (self-reported, resume parsed, assessment verified, recruiter tagged), endorsement count, and is_primary flag indicating the candidate\'s top marketable skills. Supports talent pool search, job order matching via skill-to-requirement mapping, and QoS (Quality of Submission) scoring workflows in Bullhorn. Skills may be linked to specific work_history entries or assessment results for provenance.' .

ind:Availability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Availability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks a candidate\'s current and future availability for placement along with stated job search and placement preferences. Availability attributes: status (available, on assignment, bench, unavailable), available start date, preferred shift, preferred hours per week (min/max), preferred work arrangement (on-site, remote, hybrid), geographic availability (city, state, radius), willing to relocate flag, willing to travel flag, travel percentage max. Preference attributes: preferred job titles, preferred industries, preferred employment type (temp, contract-to-hire, direct placement, FTE), desired pay rate (min/max), desired bill rate awareness flag, preferred locations, preferred company size, preferred work culture attributes, open to temp-to-perm flag, open to per diem flag, preference last updated date. Critical for bench tracking, redeployment, dispatch workflows, and proactive sourcing outreach.' .

ind:StatusHistory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Status History' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Immutable audit log of all candidate lifecycle status transitions within the ATS workflow. Captures prior status, new status, transition reason code, transition trigger (system, recruiter, candidate, client), recruiter ID who made the change, associated job order ID (if applicable), transition timestamp, and notes. Status values include: new lead, in-progress, submitted, interviewed, placed, on assignment, bench, redeployed, inactive, do-not-place, fall-off. For do-not-place (DNP) transitions, additionally captures DNP scope (client-specific, program-specific, global), DNP reason code, DNP initiator, DNP expiration date, and review-required flag. Supports fall-off rate tracking, pipeline velocity, compliance audit trails, and DNP enforcement workflows.' .

ind:Interaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Interaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all recruiter-to-candidate and system-to-candidate interaction events throughout the candidate lifecycle. Captures interaction type (call, email, SMS, in-person meeting, video interview, portal message), interaction direction (inbound, outbound), interaction channel, interaction subject/summary, recruiter ID, interaction timestamp, response received flag, response timestamp, sentiment tag (positive, neutral, negative), and linked job order ID if applicable. Supports NPS tracking, candidate experience measurement, recruiter activity KPI reporting, and SLA compliance monitoring in Bullhorn CRM. This is the transactional activity log for candidate communications — distinct from status_history which tracks lifecycle state changes.' .

ind:Assessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores results of formal candidate assessments and screening evaluations administered during the recruitment process. Captures assessment type (skills test, behavioral assessment, cognitive test, technical screen, video interview score, drug screen result, reference check score), assessment provider (HireVue, Codility, Wonderlic, etc.), assessment date, raw score, normalized score, pass/fail result, assessor ID (if human), assessment version, expiration date, and linked job order ID if assessment was req-specific. Supports QoS and candidate ranking workflows.' .

ind:Education rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Education' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Structured education history for each candidate, capturing institution name, institution type (university, community college, trade school, bootcamp, online platform), degree type (high school diploma, associate, bachelor, master, doctorate, certificate, bootcamp certificate), field of study, major, minor, graduation date, GPA (if provided), is_highest_degree flag, verified flag, and verification source. Sourced from resume parsing and candidate-submitted data. Used for qualification matching on job orders requiring specific educational credentials.' .

ind:PayRateAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Rate Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the negotiated or agreed pay rate terms between the staffing firm and the candidate for a specific engagement context. Captures pay rate type (hourly, daily, weekly, salary), base pay rate, OT (overtime) rate, DT (double time) rate, per diem rate, currency, effective date, expiration date, pay rate basis (W-2, 1099, EOR), burden rate applied, negotiated by recruiter ID, and approval status. Distinct from the billing-side bill rate — this is the candidate-facing pay agreement. Supports payroll processing handoff to TempWorks.' .

ind:RightToRepresent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Right To Represent' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks RTR (Right to Represent) grants issued by candidates authorizing the staffing firm to submit their profile to a specific client or job order. Captures candidate ID, job order ID, client ID, RTR grant method (verbal, email, portal consent, signed form), RTR grant timestamp, RTR expiration date, RTR scope (single req, client-wide, program-wide), revocation flag, revocation timestamp, and revocation reason. Critical for compliance with co-employment rules and preventing unauthorized submittals. Supports OFCCP and EEOC audit readiness.' .

ind:TalentPoolMembership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Talent Pool Membership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity tracking which curated talent pools or talent communities a candidate belongs to, including redeployment pool assignments when a candidate is being actively redeployed from an ending assignment' .

ind:DiversityProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Diversity Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores voluntary self-identification data for EEOC, OFCCP, and diversity reporting purposes. Captures race/ethnicity (self-identified, per EEOC categories), gender identity, veteran status (non-veteran, protected veteran, active duty), disability status (per ADA/Section 503), collection method (voluntary self-ID form, portal), collection date, consent to use for reporting flag, and data classification level (restricted). Maintained separately from the core profile to enforce access control and comply with FCRA, EEOC, and OFCCP regulations.' .

ind:Credential rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credential' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for every credential, certification, license, qualification, immunization, or safety certification type recognized by Staffing Hr across all staffing verticals (healthcare, IT, skilled trades, finance, government). Defines the credential taxonomy including credential name, issuing authority, governing body, credential category (license, certification, clearance, assessment, immunization, safety_certification), applicable industry vertical, required renewal cycle, expiration rules, and whether the credential is mandatory for placement eligibility. Covers professional licenses (RN, CPA, PE, CDL), safety certifications (OSHA 10/30/510), immunizations (Hep B, MMR, TB, COVID-19), security clearances, and skills assessments. This is the SSOT for credential definitions — distinct from a candidate\'s actual held credential instance.' .

ind:CredentialInstance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credential Instance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing a specific credential held by a candidate — the instance of a credential type owned by a worker. Tracks credential number, issuing authority, issue date, expiration date, current verification status (pending, verified, expired, revoked), verification method, verification date, source system (Sterling BGC, manual upload, third-party registry), and extended attributes for specialized credential types (e.g., lot number and titer results for immunizations, card number for OSHA certifications, clearance level/granting agency/investigation type/polygraph details for security clearances). Also owns the full renewal lifecycle for the credential instance: renewal application date, submission date, renewal authority, renewal fee, renewal status (initiated, submitted, approved, denied, pending_documentation), new expiration date upon approval, and CEU requirements fulfilled. This is the operational SSOT for \'does this candidate currently hold this credential?\' and \'what is the renewal status?\' — drives placement eligibility checks, expiry alerting, and renewal workflows.' .

ind:BgcOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Bgc Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record representing a background check (BGC) order placed with Sterling Background Check or another screening vendor for a specific candidate. Captures order date, package type (criminal, employment verification, education verification, drug screen, credit check, MVR), order status (ordered, in-progress, completed, disputed, cancelled), turnaround SLA, adjudication status, and the triggering job order or placement. Sourced from Sterling Background Check system.' .

ind:BgcResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Bgc Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Consolidated SSOT for all screening and verification outcome data returned from Sterling or another screening vendor. Each record represents a single component result within a background check order or standalone screening event. Captures the check component type (criminal_search, employment_verification, education_verification, reference_check, sex_offender_registry, global_watchlist, drug_screen, credit_check, MVR), result status (clear, consider, adverse, pending, negative, positive, dilute, adulterated, substituted), finding details, county/jurisdiction searched, adjudication decision, adverse action flag, FCRA compliance flags, result received timestamp, and component-specific extended attributes. Drug screen attributes: panel type (5/10/12-panel), specimen type (urine, hair, oral fluid), collection site, collection date, lab processing date, MRO review status and decision, DOT vs. non-DOT flag, substances detected. Education verification attributes: institution name, degree type, field of study, graduation date, verification source (NSC, direct institution, third-party), verification outcome. Employment verification attributes: employer name, employment dates, job title, verification method (direct, The Work Number/Equifax), discrepancies found. Reference check attributes: reference contact name, relationship to candidate, structured ratings (work quality, reliability, communication, rehire eligibility), verbatim comments, overall recommendation. One bgc_order produces multiple bgc_result records. This is the single authoritative source for all screening outcomes — no separate sub-type products exist.' .

ind:DrugScreen rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Screen' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for a drug screening event ordered for a candidate. Tracks panel type (5-panel, 10-panel, 12-panel), specimen type (urine, hair, oral fluid, breath), collection site, collection date, lab processing date, result status (negative, positive, dilute, adulterated, substituted, cancelled, pending), substances detected, MRO (Medical Review Officer) review status, MRO decision, and DOT vs. non-DOT compliance flag. Sourced from Sterling Background Check drug screen module.' .

ind:LicenseVerification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'License Verification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the verification of a professional license against an official state or national registry (e.g., nursing license via state board, CPA via NASBA, PE via NCEES, CDL via DMV). Tracks license number, issuing state/jurisdiction, license type, verification source (primary source, third-party registry, manual), verification date, verification outcome (verified, not found, expired, suspended, revoked), license status at time of verification, and next scheduled re-verification date. Critical for healthcare, finance, and government staffing verticals.' .

ind:SkillsAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Skills Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for a formal skills assessment administered to a candidate to validate proficiency in a specific skill, technology, or trade. Captures assessment type (written test, practical evaluation, simulation, coding challenge, trade skills test), assessment provider (internal, third-party like Criteria Corp or Wonderlic), skill or competency assessed, assessment date, raw score, percentile rank, pass/fail threshold, result status, and validity period. Supports QoS (Quality of Submission) tracking and candidate ranking.' .

ind:TrainingRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking completion of a required or elective training course by a candidate or placed worker. Captures training course name, training provider (internal LMS via SAP SuccessFactors, external vendor), training category (OSHA safety, HIPAA compliance, harassment prevention, skills development, onboarding orientation), delivery method (in-person, e-learning, virtual), completion date, expiration date, pass/fail status, CEU credits earned, and whether the training is mandatory for a specific placement or client. Sourced from SAP SuccessFactors LMS.' .

ind:CredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity defining which credentials, licenses, certifications, drug screens, and BGC packages are required for a specific job order or placement type. Captures the job order or placement type reference, required credential type, whether the requirement is mandatory or preferred, the required verification level (primary source vs. self-reported), acceptable expiration window, client-specific override rules, and effective date of the requirement. Enables automated credentialing gap analysis when a candidate is submitted for a role. Named to avoid collision with the placement domain\'s core entities.' .

ind:AdverseAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Adverse Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record managing the FCRA-mandated adverse action process triggered when a BGC result leads to a decision not to hire or place a candidate. Captures the pre-adverse action notice date, candidate notification method, dispute period start and end dates, candidate dispute response, final adverse action notice date, basis for adverse action (specific BGC finding reference), individualized assessment performed flag, EEOC compliance review flag, and final disposition (withdrawn, confirmed, overturned). Critical for FCRA, EEOC, and OFCCP compliance in the staffing industry. Supports the full pre-adverse → dispute → final adverse action workflow required by federal and state fair chance hiring laws. Note: This product captures the credentialing-triggered adverse action workflow; the compliance domain may own broader FCRA reporting and regulatory audit aggregation. Cross-domain SSOT boundary requires global architect resolution.' .

ind:CredentialPackage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credential Package' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining a named bundle of credentialing requirements (BGC checks, drug screens, license verifications, training completions, assessments) that must be satisfied for a specific client, industry vertical, or job category. Examples: Healthcare Travel Nurse Package, Federal Government IT Clearance Package, Light Industrial Warehouse Package. Captures package name, applicable vertical, client or program scope, list of required credential types, required BGC components, drug screen panel, effective and expiry dates, and package version for change tracking. Enables standardized credentialing workflows across similar placements and drives the candidate_readiness evaluation.' .

ind:ReadinessStatus rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Readiness Status' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational summary record representing the current overall credentialing readiness status of a candidate for a specific job order, placement, or credentialing package. Captures the candidate reference, job order or package reference, overall status (fully credentialed, partially credentialed, not credentialed, expired, pending review), count of required vs. completed credentials, outstanding items list, last status evaluation date, and placement eligibility flag. This is the operational \'go/no-go\' record used by recruiters and compliance teams before submitting or placing a candidate.' .

ind:WorkAuthorization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Work Authorization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record capturing a candidate\'s work authorization status and documentation in the United States or other jurisdictions. Tracks authorization type (US Citizen, Permanent Resident, H-1B, OPT, TN, EAD, L-1, O-1, etc.), sponsorship required flag, visa number, visa category, authorized start date, authorized end date, country of authorization, sponsoring employer (if applicable), and USCIS case number. Distinct from I-9 verification (which is the compliance process) — this is the authoritative record of the worker\'s legal right to work. Critical for placement eligibility, co-employment risk management, and ensuring compliance with immigration law in staffing engagements.' .

ind:CredentialDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credential Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for physical or digital documents submitted by a candidate to support credentialing verification — diplomas, transcripts, license copies, certification cards, immunization records, professional references, and government-issued IDs. Captures document type, document title, issuing institution or authority, issue date, expiration date, document storage reference (DocuSign CLM or document vault URI), verification status, and the credential or verification record it supports. Provides the document audit trail required for FCRA, HIPAA, and client audit purposes.' .

ind:EducationVerification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Education Verification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the verification of a candidate\'s educational credentials against issuing institutions or the National Student Clearinghouse. Tracks institution name, degree or diploma type, field of study, graduation date, verification method (NSC, direct institution contact, third-party), verification date, verification outcome (verified, not verified, discrepancy found, institution not participating), and the BGC order that triggered the verification. Supports quality of submission (QoS) standards and client-mandated degree requirements.' .

ind:EmploymentVerification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Employment Verification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the verification of a candidate\'s prior employment history as part of the BGC or credentialing process. Tracks employer name, employment dates (start and end), job title, employment type (FTE, contract, temp), verification method (direct employer contact, The Work Number/Equifax, third-party), verification date, outcome (verified, unverified, discrepancy found, employer unresponsive), and any discrepancies between candidate-stated and verified information. Sourced from Sterling BGC employment verification component.' .

ind:ReferenceCheck rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Reference Check' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing a professional reference check conducted for a candidate as part of the screening and credentialing process. Tracks reference contact name, relationship to candidate (supervisor, peer, subordinate, client), employer at time of reference, contact method, contact date, recruiter or third-party conducting the check, structured rating scores (work quality, reliability, communication, rehire eligibility), verbatim comments, overall recommendation (positive, neutral, negative), and whether the reference was used in a placement decision.' .

ind:PayRun rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Run' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each payroll processing cycle executed through TempWorks Payroll. Captures the payroll run header including pay period start and end dates, pay date, pay frequency, run type (regular, off-cycle, adjustment, void-and-reissue), run status (open, processing, approved, posted, voided), total gross pay, total net pay, total tax withholdings, total deductions, total employer burden, worker count, processing timestamps, and approver. Serves as the authoritative anchor for all payroll transactions within a given cycle and the primary reconciliation point for payroll operations.' .

ind:PayStub rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Stub' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record representing the individual worker pay statement generated for each pay run, including full pay disbursement details. Captures worker identifier, pay run reference, gross pay, regular hours, overtime hours, double-time hours, per diem amounts, gross-to-net calculation details, total deductions, total tax withholdings, net pay, and stub status. Disbursement attributes: pay delivery method (direct deposit, check, pay card), check number or ACH trace number, bank routing number, account number (masked), account type (checking, savings), deposit allocation type (full net, fixed amount, percentage split), allocation amounts for split-deposit configurations, deposit priority for multiple accounts, prenote status, account verification status, and pay card routing for unbanked workers. SSOT for individual worker earnings per pay period, associated payment disbursement instructions, and banking configuration — consolidates all direct deposit and ACH details formerly tracked separately.' .

ind:PayRate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the pay rate structure for a worker on a specific assignment or job order. Captures regular pay rate, overtime (OT) rate multiplier, double-time (DT) rate multiplier, per diem rate, shift differential rate, effective start and end dates, rate type (hourly, salary, piece-rate, daily), pay frequency (weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly), currency, rate source (negotiated, VMS-driven, standard), and approval status. Supports multi-rate scenarios for workers on multiple assignments.' .

ind:EarningsLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Earnings Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional line-item record capturing each individual earnings component within a worker pay stub. Covers regular pay, OT pay, DT pay, holiday pay, PTO payout, bonus, commission, per diem, expense reimbursement, shift differential, and other earning types. Stores hours or units, rate applied, earning code, earning description, taxability flag, and computed gross amount. Enables granular gross pay decomposition for reporting and compliance.' .

ind:TaxLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing all payroll tax obligations — both employee withholdings and employer-side taxes — per worker per pay stub within a pay run. Employee side: federal income tax, state income tax, local/city tax, FICA Social Security and Medicare employee shares, additional Medicare surtax, and supplemental withholdings. Employer side: FICA Social Security and Medicare employer match, FUTA, SUTA by state, and local employer taxes. Stores tax side discriminator (employee/employer), tax authority jurisdiction, tax type code, taxable wage base, tax rate applied, withholding method (percentage, flat, table-based), computed amount, YTD taxable wages, YTD amount, and multi-state jurisdiction details. SSOT for ALL payroll tax line items — both employee withholdings and employer taxes are unified in this single product with a tax_side discriminator. Critical for gross-to-net calculation, burden rate validation, multi-state payroll tax filing, and quarterly/annual tax reconciliation.' .

ind:DeductionLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Deduction Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional line-item record for each voluntary or involuntary deduction applied to a worker pay stub, serving as the SSOT for all payroll deductions including benefit enrollment-driven withholdings. For benefit-type deductions: stores benefit plan name, plan type (medical, dental, vision, 401k, FSA, HSA, life, supplemental), coverage tier (employee only, employee+spouse, family), employee premium contribution, employer contribution, benefit carrier, enrollment effective and termination dates, and enrollment status. For garnishment-type deductions: references the governing garnishment order. For all deductions: stores deduction code, deduction type (pre-tax, post-tax, benefit, garnishment), deduction amount, deduction frequency, YTD deduction total, court order reference for garnishments, and deduction status (active, suspended, terminated). Consolidates benefit enrollment tracking with deduction processing — enrollment attributes drive premium withholding calculations each pay period.' .

ind:BurdenRate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Burden Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the employer burden rate structure applied to worker pay for cost modeling, spread calculation, and client billing markup in staffing operations. Captures burden components including FICA employer share percentage, FUTA rate, SUTA rate by state, workers compensation (WC) rate by NCCI class code (with state-specific overrides, class description, hazard category, and base rate per $100 of payroll), general liability rate, benefits load percentage, overhead percentage, and total burden percentage. Stores effective dates, state jurisdiction, WC policy reference, client or assignment applicability, and rate source (manual, system-calculated, carrier-provided). Used to compute total employer cost per worker hour, validate bill rate margins, and support spread analysis for staffing profitability reporting.' .

ind:WcPolicy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Wc Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for workers compensation insurance policies and premium calculations administered through TempWorks Payroll — unified SSOT for both WC policy administration and premium accrual. Policy attributes: policy number, insurance carrier, policy effective and expiration dates, state jurisdiction, experience modification factor (EMR), policy type (guaranteed cost, loss-sensitive), premium basis (payroll-based), audit frequency, and policy status. Premium transaction attributes: WC class code, NCCI class description, state jurisdiction, payroll amount subject to WC, WC rate applied per $100 of payroll, computed premium amount, experience modification factor applied, YTD premium total, premium period, and pay run reference. Supports multi-state WC compliance for temporary and contract workers, carrier reporting, premium audit reconciliation, accurate burden rate application, and cost allocation to client assignments.' .

ind:TaxFiling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Filing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking payroll tax deposit and filing obligations submitted to federal, state, and local tax authorities. Captures filing type (941, 940, SUTA, state income tax), tax authority, filing period, total taxable wages, total tax liability, deposit amount, deposit date, filing due date, filing status (pending, deposited, filed, amended), confirmation number, and penalty/interest amounts if applicable. Supports multi-state tax compliance and IRS/DOL audit readiness.' .

ind:TaxForm rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Form' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record representing annual tax forms generated for both W-2 employees/temporary workers and 1099 independent contractors. For W-2 forms: captures Box 1 wages, Box 2 federal income tax withheld, Boxes 3-6 Social Security and Medicare wages and withholdings, state and local wages and withholdings, pre-tax benefit amounts (Box 12 codes), and W-2 filing status. For 1099 forms: captures 1099-NEC nonemployee compensation (Box 1), 1099-MISC miscellaneous income, backup withholding, and state income. Stores tax year, worker/contractor identifier, employer/payer EIN, form type discriminator (W-2, W-2c, 1099-NEC, 1099-MISC), filing status (draft, filed, corrected), e-file confirmation, and correction history. SSOT for ALL annual tax form reporting — unified W-2 and 1099 populations common in staffing operations where both employee and IC worker types coexist. Supports IRS e-filing, state filing, worker distribution, and year-end reconciliation.' .

ind:PtoAccrual rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pto Accrual' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record managing PTO policy definitions and worker-level accrual balances — unified SSOT for both policy rules and individual accrual tracking. Policy attributes: policy name, accrual method (hours-based, tenure-based, front-loaded), accrual rate per hour worked or per period, maximum accrual cap, rollover rules (use-it-or-lose-it, rollover with cap, unlimited), waiting period before accrual begins, payout-on-termination flag, state jurisdiction applicability, worker classification eligibility (W-2 temp, FTE, contract), and policy effective dates. Accrual transaction attributes: worker identifier, accrual period, hours accrued, hours used, hours forfeited, current PTO balance, YTD accrued and used hours, accrual trigger (pay stub reference), and balance as-of date. Supports compliance with state-mandated paid sick leave laws (California, New York, Oregon, etc.), PTO payout on separation, and staffing-specific scenarios where temporary workers accrue PTO across multiple client assignments.' .

ind:GarnishmentOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Garnishment Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for court-ordered or agency-mandated wage garnishments applied to worker pay. Captures garnishment type (child support, creditor garnishment, student loan, tax levy, bankruptcy), issuing authority, case or order number, ordered amount or percentage, maximum withholding limit (per CCPA/FLSA disposable earnings rules), priority order when multiple garnishments exist, remittance payee, remittance address, effective date, expiration date, and garnishment status (active, suspended, satisfied, terminated).' .

ind:PayAdjustment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Adjustment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing manual corrections, retroactive pay adjustments, voids, and reissues applied outside of a standard pay run. Covers adjustment types including pay correction, void and reissue, retroactive rate change, missed hours correction, tax correction, and deduction correction. Stores original pay stub reference, adjustment reason code, adjusted earnings or deduction amounts, approver, approval date, and adjustment processing status. Maintains audit trail for payroll corrections and supports SOX-adjacent controls.' .

ind:TaxWithholdingElection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Withholding Election' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record capturing a worker\'s federal and state tax withholding elections as submitted via W-4 (federal) and equivalent state withholding forms. Stores filing status (single, married, head of household), number of allowances or Step 3 dependent credits (post-2020 W-4), additional withholding amount, exempt from withholding flag, state withholding form type, state-specific elections, effective date, and election source (paper form, electronic self-service). Drives tax withholding calculation in each pay run.' .

ind:EorArrangement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Eor Arrangement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining Employer of Record (EOR) and co-employment payroll arrangements where Staffing Hr acts as the legal employer of record for workers placed at client sites. Captures arrangement type (EOR, co-employment, PEO), client reference, worker population covered, legal employer entity, payroll processing entity, benefit plan sponsorship responsibility, workers comp policy assignment, tax filing responsibility allocation, liability indemnification terms, effective dates, and arrangement status. Supports complex multi-entity payroll structures.' .

ind:SourcingCampaign rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Sourcing Campaign' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for talent sourcing campaigns initiated to fill job orders. Captures campaign name, type (job board, social media, referral, RPO, MSP), target skill sets, geographic scope, budget, start/end dates, channel mix, campaign owner, associated requisition targets, and campaign status. Supports sourcing strategy planning and channel effectiveness analysis.' .

ind:JobPosting rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Posting' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents a published job advertisement derived from a job order requisition. Tracks posting title, description, required skills, location, employment type (temp, contract-to-hire, direct placement), pay range, bill rate range, posting channel (job board, career site, VMS, social), posting date, expiration date, posting status (active, paused, closed, filled), and ATS reference from Bullhorn. Supports multi-channel job distribution and posting lifecycle management.' .

ind:Submittal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Submittal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional record representing a candidate submittal (submission) to a client for a specific job order. Captures submittal date, submitting recruiter, candidate profile reference, job order reference, client contact submitted to, submittal status (submitted, viewed, shortlisted, rejected, interview requested), right-to-represent (RTR) flag, RTR date, QoS (Quality of Submission) rating, pay rate proposed, bill rate proposed, and Bullhorn ATS submittal ID. Central entity for tracking recruiter activity and submittal-to-hire conversion ratios.' .

ind:RtrAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Rtr Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks Right-to-Represent (RTR) agreements between a staffing firm and a candidate for a specific client or job order. Records RTR grant date, expiration date, RTR status (pending, granted, expired, revoked), candidate acknowledgment method (email, portal, verbal), exclusivity flag, and any RTR conflicts with competing agencies. Ensures legal protection of candidate representation rights and prevents co-representation disputes.' .

ind:Interview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Interview' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Represents a client interview event for a submitted candidate, covering the full interview lifecycle from scheduling through feedback collection and hiring recommendation. Captures interview date/time, type (phone screen, video, onsite, panel), format, client interviewer names, candidate confirmation status, coordinator, location or video link, reschedule/cancellation tracking, overall rating, individual competency ratings, hire recommendation (yes/no/maybe), detailed feedback notes, feedback submission date, decision outcome (advance, reject, hold), and rejection reason code. Central to interview coordination workflows, scheduling efficiency metrics, QoS scoring, and submittal-to-hire ratio analytics. Single source of truth for all interview scheduling and feedback data.' .

ind:InterviewFeedback rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Interview Feedback' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures client feedback and evaluation results following a candidate interview. Records overall rating, individual competency ratings, hire recommendation (yes/no/maybe), feedback notes, feedback submission date, interviewer name, decision outcome (advance, reject, hold), and rejection reason code. Feeds into QoS scoring and submittal-to-hire ratio analytics.' .

ind:HiringDecision rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Hiring Decision' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the final hiring decision made by the client for a candidate submittal. Captures decision date, decision type (hired, rejected, on-hold, backfill), decision maker (client contact), rejection reason category, rejection reason detail, time-to-fill (TTF) calculated value in days, time-to-start (TTS) calculated value in days, and whether the hire resulted from a temp-to-perm conversion. Links the recruitment lifecycle to placement initiation.' .

ind:ReqPipeline rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Req Pipeline' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Real-time snapshot of candidate progression through recruitment stages for a specific job order or requisition. Tracks pipeline stage (sourced, screened, submitted, interviewing, offered, hired, rejected, withdrawn), stage entry/exit timestamps, stage duration in business days, candidate counts per stage, and pipeline health indicators including stage conversion rates, aging alerts, and bottleneck flags. Primary tool for recruiter workload management, hiring manager visibility dashboards, VMS scorecard reporting, and time-to-fill forecasting in RPO and MSP delivery models. Refreshed on each stage transition event to maintain current-state accuracy.' .

ind:CandidateScreening rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Candidate Screening' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the results of candidate screening activities performed during the recruitment process. Captures screening type (phone screen, skills assessment, behavioral interview, technical test), screening date, screener name, screening outcome (pass, fail, conditional), scoring details, notes, disqualification reason, and whether the candidate was advanced to submittal. Distinct from credentialing (BGC, drug screen) which is owned by the credentialing domain.' .

ind:SourcingActivity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Sourcing Activity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular transactional record of individual sourcing actions taken by recruiters to identify and engage candidates. Captures activity type (LinkedIn outreach, job board search, referral contact, ATS search, Boolean search, campus event), activity date, recruiter performing the activity, sourcing channel used, number of candidates identified, number of candidates contacted, response rate, and associated sourcing campaign. Feeds channel effectiveness and recruiter productivity reporting.' .

ind:RecruiterAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruiter Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines recruiter ownership and accountability for filling a specific job order or requisition. Tracks assigned recruiter, assignment date, type (primary, backup, split-desk, RPO team, MSP coordinator), status (active, reassigned, closed), reassignment reason, target submittal count, and performance against target. Supports workload balancing across desks, recruiter performance tracking, split-fee arrangements, and RPO/MSP delivery team management.' .

ind:RecruitmentSlaTarget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruitment Sla Target' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines Service Level Agreement (SLA) targets for recruitment delivery performance against specific clients, programs, or job order categories. Captures SLA type (time-to-fill target, time-to-start target, submittal count target, QoS minimum rating, interview-to-offer ratio, fill rate), target value, measurement unit, client-specific or program-default flag, SLA effective and expiration dates, measurement frequency (weekly, monthly, quarterly), and breach threshold with severity tiers. Supports MSP scorecard compliance, RPO program SLA monitoring, and client business review reporting.' .

ind:SlaBreach rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Breach' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an SLA breach event in the recruitment process. Captures breach date, breach type (TTF exceeded, submittal count missed, QoS below threshold), associated SLA definition, job order reference, client reference, breach severity (minor, major, critical), root cause category, remediation action taken, and breach resolution date. Supports client reporting and continuous improvement programs.' .

ind:Invoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core billing document issued to a client for staffing services rendered during a billing period. Captures invoice number, date, due date, billing period, total amount, tax amount, net amount, payment terms, status (draft, sent, paid, partially paid, disputed, void), billing model (time-and-materials, per-diem, project-based, SOW-based, direct placement fee), currency, PO number, and client billing account reference. SSOT for all client-facing billing documents across all staffing engagement types. Supports void-and-rebill workflows for retroactive billing corrections.' .

ind:InvoiceLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Invoice Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Line-item detail within a client invoice representing a single billable unit of work. Each line ties to a specific worker assignment, timesheet period, or deliverable. Captures line number, service description, billing type (regular, OT, DT, per diem, expense, placement fee), quantity, bill rate, extended amount, pay period dates, worker and job order references, cost center, GL account, tax code, and markup/spread values.' .

ind:BillRate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Bill Rate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of negotiated bill rates for client engagements. Stores the agreed-upon rate for a specific job category, skill level, client, and contract. Includes rate amount, rate type (standard, OT, DT, per diem, blended), effective dates, currency, rate card reference, markup percentage, spread amount (bill minus pay rate), gross margin percentage, burden inclusion flag, and approval status. Authoritative rate source for invoice generation and profitability calculations.' .

ind:BillingRateSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing Rate Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference entity defining structured rate schedules and rate card templates used across client engagements. Captures rate schedule name, schedule type (standard, premium, MSP-managed, VMS-driven, SOW), applicable job categories, skill tiers, geographic market, effective date range, markup percentage tiers, OT multiplier, DT multiplier, per diem allowance, holiday rate multiplier, and associated MSA or contract reference. Used as the template from which individual bill rates are instantiated for specific worker assignments.' .

ind:Payment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of client payments received against outstanding invoices. Captures payment date, payment amount, payment method (ACH, wire, check, credit card), payment reference number, bank account details (masked), remittance advice reference, applied invoice references, unapplied amount, currency, exchange rate, payment status (pending, cleared, returned, voided), and source transaction identifier. SSOT for all client payment receipts in the billing domain.' .

ind:PaymentApplication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Payment Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association record linking client payments to specific invoices or invoice lines, capturing the allocation of a payment across one or more outstanding invoices. Stores applied amount, discount taken, write-off amount, application date, application type (full, partial, prepayment, credit memo offset), and reconciliation status. Enables accurate accounts receivable aging and cash application tracking.' .

ind:CreditMemo rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Credit Memo' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of credit memos issued to clients to offset or reduce outstanding invoice balances. Captures credit memo number, issue date, credit amount, reason code (billing error, retroactive rate correction, timesheet rebilling, service credit, fall-off adjustment, conversion fee reversal), originating invoice reference, approval status, applied status, expiration date, and issuing user. Supports dispute resolution, retroactive rate adjustments, timesheet correction rebilling, and accounts receivable balance corrections. Used in conjunction with invoice void-and-rebill workflows for full retroactive billing adjustments.' .

ind:BillingDispute rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing Dispute' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational record tracking client billing disputes raised against invoices or invoice lines. Captures dispute number, dispute open date, dispute type (rate discrepancy, hours mismatch, unauthorized charge, duplicate invoice, worker eligibility), disputed amount, client contact, assigned resolution owner, dispute status (open, under review, resolved, escalated, closed), resolution date, resolution type (credit issued, invoice adjusted, dispute rejected), and root cause category. Drives the dispute-to-resolution workflow and feeds collections hold logic.' .

ind:CollectionActivity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Collection Activity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Operational record of collections actions taken against past-due client billing accounts. Captures activity date, type (phone call, email, demand letter, escalation, legal referral, payment plan setup, write-off recommendation), collector, client contact, outcome (promise to pay, dispute raised, payment received, no response, escalated, payment plan agreed), follow-up date, notes, and associated invoice references. Drives the collections workflow, DSO reduction efforts, and aging bucket management.' .

ind:SpreadRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Spread Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the calculated spread (bill rate minus pay rate) and gross margin for each billable worker-assignment-period combination. Stores bill rate, pay rate, spread amount, markup percentage, burden rate, burdened cost, gross margin amount and percentage, billing period, assignment and job order references, client reference, and worker classification (W-2, 1099, corp-to-corp). SSOT for staffing profitability analytics at the transaction level. Supports real-time margin monitoring, client profitability reporting, and recruiter commission calculations.' .

ind:BillingAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Billing Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record representing a client\'s financial billing entity — the account to which invoices are issued and against which payments and credits are tracked. Distinct from the CRM client profile (owned by client domain). Captures billing account number, billing address, AR contact, payment terms (net days, early payment discount percentage, discount window), credit limit, credit status, preferred payment method, tax ID, tax exemption status, invoice delivery method, currency, billing cycle (weekly, bi-weekly, monthly), and external customer account identifier. SSOT for client billing identity and payment terms within the billing domain.' .

ind:PlacementFee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Placement Fee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for direct placement and permanent hire fee billing. Captures fee type (direct placement, temp-to-perm conversion, RPO fee, retained search), fee amount, fee percentage of first-year salary, guarantee period (fall-off window in days), fall-off date, replacement eligibility, invoiced amount, invoice reference, payment status, and associated job order and candidate references. SSOT for permanent placement revenue, distinct from time-and-materials billing. Supports fall-off tracking and guarantee period management critical to direct hire operations.' .

ind:ExpenseCharge rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Expense Charge' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of billable expenses incurred by workers or staffing operations and passed through to client invoices. Captures expense type (per diem, travel, lodging, mileage, equipment, training), date, amount, currency, receipt reference, approval status, billable flag, markup percentage, client PO reference, cost center, GL account, and associated assignment and invoice line references. Supports pass-through expense billing in project-based and SOW engagements.' .

ind:SowBillingMilestone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Sow Billing Milestone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking billing milestones for Statement of Work (SOW) engagements. Captures milestone name, milestone number, SOW reference, milestone type (deliverable, phase completion, time-based, percent-complete), scheduled billing date, actual billing date, milestone amount, completion percentage, approval status, approver, invoice reference, and milestone status (pending, approved, invoiced, disputed). Enables project-based and SOW billing models distinct from time-and-materials hourly billing.' .

ind:WriteOff rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Billing ;
    rdfs:label 'Write Off' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record documenting the write-off of uncollectible accounts receivable balances. Captures write-off date, write-off amount, write-off reason (bad debt, client bankruptcy, disputed and settled, aged beyond policy, small balance), original invoice reference, client billing account reference, approval authority, GL account code, tax impact flag, and recovery status (in case of subsequent collection). Supports bad debt management, financial reporting, and AR balance accuracy.' .

ind:OrderHeader rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Header' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master entity representing a client requisition (req) — the authoritative job order header record and central hub of the joborder domain. Captures the full lifecycle of a client demand request from intake through closure. Stores requisition number, job title, position type (temp, contract-to-hire, direct placement, SOW), employment classification (W-2, 1099, C2C), headcount target (total positions authorized, positions filled, positions remaining), backfill indicator, priority level, order status (open, filled, cancelled, on-hold, closed), intake date, target start date, assignment end date, and originating source (VMS, CRM, direct). Central hub connecting client demand to candidate supply in the ATS/CRM. All other joborder products reference this entity via req_id.' .

ind:PositionRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Position Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the detailed position specifications attached to a requisition. Captures job description, required education level, years of experience, work location type (on-site, remote, hybrid), shift type, travel requirements, physical demands, security clearance level, drug screen requirement, background check requirement, and any client-specific screening criteria. Represents the structured demand profile that drives candidate matching and submittal qualification.' .

ind:SkillRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Skill Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures the individual skill, competency, and technology requirements associated with a requisition. Stores skill name, skill category (technical, soft, industry-specific), proficiency level required (beginner, intermediate, expert), whether the skill is mandatory or preferred, years of experience required for the skill, and certification requirement flag. Enables structured skill-based candidate matching and QoS (Quality of Submission) scoring within the ATS.' .

ind:RateOverride rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Rate Override' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores the approved bill rate, pay rate, markup percentage, spread (bill rate minus pay rate), burden rate, and gross margin targets for a requisition. Captures OT (overtime) bill rate, DT (double time) bill rate, per diem allowance, and any client-negotiated rate caps or floors. Tracks rate effective dates, rate approval status, and the rate source (MSA rate schedule, VMS rate card, negotiated). Serves as the financial backbone of the job order connecting to billing and payroll domains.' .

ind:SlaCommitment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Commitment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the SLA (Service Level Agreement) commitments and submittal governance rules attached to a requisition or client program. Captures TTF (Time to Fill) target in business days, TTS (Time to Start) target, submittal SLA (hours to first submittal), minimum submittals required per req, maximum submittals per vendor (VMS programs), submittal window open/close dates, exclusive submittal period flag, RTR (Right to Represent) enforcement flag, duplicate submittal prevention rules, interview-to-offer ratio target, fill rate target, and penalty terms for SLA breach. Tracks SLA tier (standard, premium, VMS-managed), SLA status (on-track, at-risk, breached), and measurement methodology. Enables operational SLA monitoring, QoS (Quality of Submission) governance, VMS program compliance, and client reporting.' .

ind:OrderStatusHistory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Status History' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative lifecycle event log for a job order, capturing every status transition and fulfillment milestone from intake through closure. Records event type (status change, milestone reached), previous status, new status, milestone type (req received, sourcing started, first submittal, interview scheduled, offer extended, placement confirmed, worker started, assignment ended), transition timestamp, target date, actual completion date, variance in business days, reason code, triggering user or system, responsible recruiter, and associated notes. Single source of truth for TTF (Time to Fill) and TTS (Time to Start) measurement, SLA breach analysis, recruiter performance benchmarking, and operational reporting. Subsumes all milestone tracking — no separate milestone entity exists.' .

ind:OrderModification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Modification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all amendments, modifications, and change orders applied to an existing requisition. Captures modification type (rate change, headcount change, duration extension, scope change, location change, title change), the field modified, old value, new value, modification date, requestor (client contact or internal recruiter), approval status, and approval date. Tracks the complete change history of a req from original intake through final closure. Supports contract amendment traceability and client billing adjustments.' .

ind:FulfillmentTeam rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Fulfillment Team' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association entity linking a requisition to the internal recruiter(s), account manager(s), and sourcing team responsible for fulfillment. Captures assigned recruiter, assignment role (lead recruiter, sourcing specialist, account manager, coordinator), assignment start date, assignment end date, assignment status (active, reassigned, closed), and workload weight for split-credit scenarios. Enables recruiter workload management, performance attribution, and commission split tracking.' .

ind:VmsOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Vms Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures VMS (Vendor Management System)-specific metadata for requisitions managed through platforms such as Beeline, Fieldglass, or Wand. Stores VMS requisition ID, VMS program name, MSP (Managed Service Provider) name, vendor tier eligibility, submission window timestamps, max submittal count per vendor, VMS rate caps, markup caps, RTR (Right to Represent) requirement flag, VMS order status, and cross-reference mapping to internal ATS req ID. Essential for MSP/VMS program compliance, automated req import reconciliation, and dual-system synchronization between the VMS platform and internal ATS.' .

ind:OrderLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the work location details for a requisition, supporting multi-site deployments where a single req may have workers at multiple client facilities. Captures site name, street address, city, state, zip code, country, location type (client site, remote, hybrid, field), work site safety classification (OSHA category), and location-specific requirements (parking, badge access, union jurisdiction, prevailing wage applicability, per diem eligibility). References client domain for master site data via FK; stores req-specific overrides and work-condition details that affect candidate matching, compliance determination, payroll tax jurisdiction (SUTA state, local tax), and workers compensation classification.' .

ind:OrderExtension rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Order Extension' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks assignment extension events for temporary and contract requisitions — one of the most common operational transactions in staffing. Captures extension request date, extension approved date, extension start date, new end date, extension duration in weeks, extended bill rate, extended pay rate, rate change indicator, extension reason (client request, project continuation, backfill pending, budget renewal), extension approval status, approving authority, and whether the extension triggers a temp-to-perm conversion clock reset or benefits eligibility change. Enables extension lifecycle management, revenue forecasting for ongoing assignments, and client billing adjustments for rate changes on extension.' .

ind:OnboardingEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Onboarding Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a single worker onboarding engagement tied to a placement or assignment. Tracks onboarding status, start date, target ready-for-assignment date, onboarding type (temp, perm, contract-to-hire, redeployment), assigned coordinator, and completion milestones. SSOT for onboarding status across the staffing lifecycle. One record per worker per placement. Central hub entity — all onboarding activities (tasks, documents, screenings, I-9, orientation, training, equipment, communications) link back to this record.' .

ind:OffboardingRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Offboarding Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a worker\'s assignment-end and separation workflow. Captures offboarding type (assignment end, voluntary resignation, client termination, conversion to perm, redeployment), coordinator assignment, equipment return tracking references, final timesheet reconciliation status, rehire eligibility determination, exit interview status, COBRA notification flag, and last day worked. One record per assignment end event. Links to redeployment_candidate when the worker is flagged for bench management.' .

ind:TaskChecklist rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Task Checklist' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reusable template defining a named collection of required onboarding or offboarding tasks for a specific scenario (e.g., temp healthcare onboarding, IT contractor onboarding, light industrial assignment end). Includes applicable placement type, division, client-specific flag, version number, effective date, and active status. Task_assignment records are instantiated from these templates for each worker engagement. Driven by requirement_rule configuration.' .

ind:TaskAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Task Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual onboarding or offboarding task assigned to a specific worker within their onboarding_record or offboarding_record. Tracks task category (document collection, orientation, training, equipment, compliance, credentialing), responsible party (worker, recruiter, coordinator, client), due date, completion status, and blocking dependencies. Instantiated from task_checklist templates.' .

ind:TaxFormSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Form Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records worker tax form submissions collected during onboarding. Covers W-4 (federal withholding), state withholding equivalents, W-9 (independent contractor), and 1099 setup forms. Tracks form type, tax year, filing status, allowances or exemptions claimed, additional withholding amount, submission date, effective date, and whether the form supersedes a prior submission. Feeds payroll tax configuration in TempWorks Payroll.' .

ind:DirectDepositSetup rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Direct Deposit Setup' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures worker direct deposit banking instructions collected during onboarding. Tracks bank name, routing number (masked), account number (masked/tokenized), account type (checking, savings), allocation type (full amount, fixed amount, percentage), allocation value, priority sequence (for split deposits), effective date, and verification status (prenote sent, prenote cleared, active, rejected). Supports split-deposit configurations with multiple records per worker. Feeds TempWorks Payroll for pay distribution.' .

ind:DocumentCollection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Document Collection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks each document collected, signed, or acknowledged during the onboarding or offboarding process. Covers document type (MSA acknowledgment, NDA, non-compete, handbook acknowledgment, safety policy, drug screen consent, BGC authorization, FCRA disclosure, offer letter, assignment confirmation, W-4, state withholding, W-9, 1099 setup), document source system (DocuSign CLM, SAP SuccessFactors, TempWorks, manual upload), DocuSign envelope ID, signed date, expiration date, storage location reference, document status, and tax-form-specific fields (tax year, filing status, allowances or exemptions claimed, additional withholding amount, effective date, supersedes prior flag, form submission date). Consolidates all onboarding document types including tax form submissions into a single collection entity differentiated by document_type. Feeds payroll tax configuration in TempWorks Payroll for tax form document types (W-4, state withholding, W-9, 1099).' .

ind:OrientationSession rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Orientation Session' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Scheduled or completed orientation session for one or more workers. Tracks orientation type (in-person, virtual, client-site, self-paced), session date, location or virtual link, facilitator, duration, topics covered, and per-worker attendance status. May be staffing-agency-led or client-led. Linked to onboarding_record for milestone completion tracking.' .

ind:LmsEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Lms Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks worker training course enrollments assigned through SAP SuccessFactors LMS during onboarding. Captures course name, course code, course category (safety, compliance, skills, client-specific, OSHA, harassment prevention), enrollment date, due date, completion date, pass/fail status, score, number of attempts, and whether the course is mandatory for assignment start. Bridges onboarding and LMS training compliance requirements.' .

ind:EquipmentProvisioning rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Equipment Provisioning' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks equipment and access provisioning requests and fulfillment for workers during onboarding or offboarding. Covers equipment type (laptop, badge, PPE, uniform, mobile device, access card, safety gear), asset tag, provisioning request date, fulfillment date, provisioning status, assigned location, return due date (for offboarding), return received date, and condition at return. Supports both client-provisioned and agency-provisioned equipment workflows.' .

ind:StatusEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Status Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Immutable event log capturing every status transition, communication, and milestone event in the onboarding or offboarding lifecycle for a worker. Records event type (status_change, outbound_email, outbound_sms, inbound_response, portal_notification, task_reminder, document_request, welcome_message, orientation_invite, bgc_status_update, offer_letter_delivery, phone_call), prior status, new status, transition timestamp, triggering actor (system, recruiter, coordinator, worker), trigger source (task completion, document signing, BGC clearance, LMS completion, manual override), communication channel (email, SMS, portal, phone), delivery status, worker response flag, linked task or document reference, and notes. Consolidates all onboarding timeline events including outbound/inbound communications into a single unified event stream. Provides the single onboarding timeline for audit trail, SLA measurement (TTF, TTS), coordinator engagement tracking, and communication history.' .

ind:OnboardingSlaTarget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Onboarding Sla Target' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines SLA targets for onboarding task and overall onboarding completion by placement type, client, job category, or geography. Captures SLA name, applicable scope (global, client-specific, job-category-specific), target days to complete overall onboarding, target days per task category (document collection, BGC, drug screen, orientation, training), breach escalation rules, and effective date range. Used to measure TTS (Time to Start) compliance.' .

ind:RequirementRule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Requirement Rule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the specific onboarding requirements and SLA targets mandated for a given client, job category, work location, or regulatory jurisdiction. Captures requirement category (i9, bgc_package, drug_screen_panel, certifications, training_courses, orientation_type, ppe, sla_timing), whether it is mandatory or conditional, the triggering condition (e.g., client-specific, state law, OSHA, DOT), target days to complete overall onboarding, target days per task category (document collection, BGC, drug screen, orientation, training), breach escalation rules (escalation contacts, escalation timing, auto-hold triggers), SLA scope (global, client-specific, job-category-specific, geography-specific), effective date, and expiration date. Drives dynamic task_checklist generation, SLA compliance measurement, and TTS (Time to Start) reporting for each onboarding engagement. Consolidates both what must be done and how fast it must be done into a single configuration entity.' .

ind:CommunicationLog rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Communication Log' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all outbound and inbound communications sent to or received from workers during the onboarding process. Captures communication channel (email, SMS, portal notification, phone), communication type (welcome message, task reminder, document request, BGC status update, orientation invite, offer letter delivery), sent timestamp, delivery status, worker response flag, and linked task or document. Supports onboarding engagement tracking and SLA breach prevention.' .

ind:Msa rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Msa' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master Service Agreement — the primary commercial contract governing the overall client-staffing firm relationship. Stores MSA header data including effective dates, governing law, jurisdiction, auto-renewal terms, termination notice periods, liability caps, indemnification clauses, insurance requirements (GL, WC, E&O minimums), and MSA status lifecycle (draft, under_review, executed, expired, terminated). Links to client account hierarchy. SSOT for all client MSA terms managed via DocuSign CLM. Parent contract for SOWs, rate schedules, SLAs, and amendments.' .

ind:Sow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Sow' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Statement of Work — a child contract under an MSA that defines a specific engagement scope, deliverables, milestones, project timelines, fixed-fee or time-and-materials pricing, and acceptance criteria. Tracks SOW status (draft, submitted, approved, active, closed), SOW type (project-based, staff augmentation, RPO, MSP), and links to the governing MSA. Managed via DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:Nda rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Nda' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Non-Disclosure Agreement — standalone or ancillary confidentiality agreement executed with clients, candidates, or vendors. Captures NDA type (mutual, one-way), parties involved, confidentiality scope, duration, carve-outs, and execution status. Tracks expiration and renewal obligations. Managed via DocuSign CLM.' .

ind:NonCompete rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Non Compete' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Non-Compete and Non-Solicitation Agreement — contractual restriction placed on placed workers (W-2 temps, contractors), direct-hire candidates, or departing internal employees. Stores restricted activity scope (client solicitation, candidate poaching, competitive employment), geographic restriction radius or territory, duration in months, enforceability jurisdiction and governing law, and linkage to the originating placement, assignment, or employment record. Tracks execution status, expiration date, and any waiver or release granted. Critical for protecting client relationships and preventing revenue leakage in staffing where placed workers and recruiters frequently move between competing firms.' .

ind:Sla rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Service Level Agreement record defining measurable performance commitments within an MSA or SOW, along with periodic measurement results tracking actual performance against those targets. Stores SLA metric name (TTF, TTS, QoS, fill rate, NPS, submittal-to-interview ratio, first-day no-show rate), target threshold, measurement frequency (weekly, monthly, quarterly), penalty/credit terms, and governing contract reference. Captures measurement results per period: actual metric value, variance from target, breach flag, penalty/credit amount triggered, measurement period dates, and measurement source system. SSOT for all contractual SLA obligations, compliance tracking, and performance measurement. Enables SLA compliance reporting, penalty/credit calculation, client QBR (Quarterly Business Review) preparation, and trend analysis across measurement periods.' .

ind:ContractRateSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Rate Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contractual rate schedule defining agreed bill rates, pay rates, markup percentages, spread, burden rates, OT/DT multipliers, and per diem allowances for specific job categories, skill levels, or labor classifications under an MSA or SOW. Tracks effective date ranges, rate card version, and approval status. SSOT for all contractually agreed pricing terms.' .

ind:Amendment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Amendment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contract Amendment — a formal, versioned modification to an existing MSA, SOW, rate schedule, or vendor agreement. Captures amendment sequence number, amendment type (rate change, scope change, term extension, party addition/removal, insurance requirement change), detailed description of changes with before/after values, effective date, expiration of prior terms, approval chain with legal and finance sign-off, and execution status via DocuSign CLM. Maintains a complete amendment audit trail for any parent contract document, enabling full contract version history reconstruction. Critical for staffing firms managing hundreds of active client and vendor contracts with frequent rate and scope changes.' .

ind:Renewal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Renewal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contract renewal, expiry, and critical date lifecycle record tracking upcoming renewal events, expiration milestones, and proactive date management for MSAs, SOWs, and vendor agreements. Stores renewal type (auto-renewal, manual renewal, evergreen, one-time), renewal trigger date, notice deadline, opt-out deadline, renewal term length, renewed rate schedule reference, negotiation status, and outcome (renewed, renegotiated, lapsed, terminated). Tracks all critical contract dates requiring proactive action — including auto-renewal opt-out deadlines, insurance certificate renewal dates, rate schedule review dates, and compliance filing deadlines — with alert type, trigger date, lead-time days, assigned owner, acknowledgment status, and resolution action taken. Enables proactive renewal pipeline management, prevents costly contract lapses or unwanted auto-renewals, and drives critical date alerting across the entire contract portfolio.' .

ind:Envelope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Envelope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'DocuSign CLM e-signature envelope record representing a single signature workflow execution with full signatory audit trail. Captures envelope ID (DocuSign native), document type, sent timestamp, completed timestamp, voided/declined status, and IP address capture for audit. Includes per-recipient signatory detail: signer name, title, organization, signing order, authentication method (email, SMS, ID verification, knowledge-based), signing authority level (e.g., VP and above, C-suite only), delegation scope (full authority, limited to SOW under $X), active/inactive signer status, individual sign/decline timestamp, and recipient status. Person/contact identity is resolved via the client or candidate domain contact master — this product stores signing-role attributes and execution events only. SSOT for all electronic execution events and signatory audit trails across MSAs, SOWs, NDAs, amendments, IC agreements, and non-competes.' .

ind:Template rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Template' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contract template and clause library master record defining the standard structure, default clauses, configurable parameters, and complete reusable clause inventory for each contract type (MSA, SOW, NDA, non-compete, amendment, IC agreement, vendor agreement). Stores template name, version, applicable contract type, default jurisdiction, required clause set, optional clause menu, and approval status. Includes the full clause library: standard and custom clause text for all clause types (indemnification, limitation of liability, IP ownership, co-employment, EEOC, OFCCP, FLSA, workers comp, governing law, data privacy, non-solicitation), clause version, jurisdiction applicability, mandatory vs. optional flag, regulatory source reference, and clause approval status. Used by DocuSign CLM to generate new contract drafts consistently while enabling clause-level compliance tracking, template governance, and regulatory clause audit. SSOT for all contract generation configuration and reusable clause management.' .

ind:Obligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contractual obligation record tracking specific commitments, deliverables, or compliance requirements arising from an MSA, SOW, SLA, or vendor agreement. Captures obligation type (periodic reporting, insurance certificate renewal, background check requirement, OFCCP/AAP compliance filing, audit right exercise, indemnification trigger, workers compensation certificate, professional liability proof, WOTC documentation), due date or recurring schedule, responsible party (internal department or external counterparty), fulfillment status, evidence of completion with document reference, and escalation path for overdue items. Enables proactive obligation management, audit readiness, and contractual compliance scoring across the entire contract portfolio.' .

ind:VendorAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor/subcontractor agreement governing the commercial relationship with third-party staffing suppliers, subvendors, independent contractor firms, and service providers within MSP/VMS-managed programs. Captures agreement type (subvendor staffing agreement, IC firm agreement, EOR/Employer of Record agreement, PEO agreement, RPO subcontract), tier classification (Tier 1/2/3), markup caps and fee schedules, payment terms (net-30/45/60), insurance requirements (GL, WC, E&O minimums), diversity certification status (MBE, WBE, SDVOB), and compliance obligations (E-Verify, background check standards, drug screening requirements). Distinct from client-facing MSAs — this is the supply-side commercial contract governing the staffing supply chain. Note: vendor identity and profile data is owned by the vendor domain; this product owns the commercial agreement terms only.' .

ind:IcAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Ic Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Independent Contractor (1099/IC) agreement record governing the engagement of independent contractors. Captures IC classification basis (IRS worker classification rules, ABC test, economic realities test), contract type (project-based, retainer), scope of services, payment terms, IP assignment, non-solicitation terms, and IRS Form 1099 reporting flag. Critical for co-employment risk management and IRS compliance.' .

ind:ContractDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical or digital contract document record representing a specific executed or draft document file associated with any contract type (MSA, SOW, NDA, amendment, IC agreement). Stores document name, file format, version number, storage location (DocuSign CLM vault reference), document status (draft, pending signature, fully executed, superseded), and retention policy classification per FCRA, GDPR, and CCPA requirements.' .

ind:ContractApprovalWorkflow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Approval Workflow' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contract approval workflow record tracking the internal review and approval chain required before a contract document can be sent for execution via DocuSign CLM. Captures workflow type (new MSA approval, SOW approval, amendment approval, rate change approval, vendor agreement approval), sequential approval stages with approver roles (legal counsel, finance/controller, operations VP, executive sponsor), per-stage decision (approved, rejected, returned for revision, escalated), approver comments, decision timestamps, and SLA for approval turnaround. Supports delegation rules, out-of-office routing, and parallel approval paths. Critical for staffing firms where rate changes and new MSAs require multi-department sign-off before client commitment.' .

ind:CreditProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Credit Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Client credit and financial risk assessment record used to evaluate and monitor a client\'s creditworthiness and ability to pay invoices on agreed terms. Captures credit score (D&B PAYDEX, internal composite score), credit limit, approved payment terms (net days), credit hold flag, credit hold reason, last credit review date, next scheduled review date, DSO (Days Sales Outstanding) actual, aging bucket summary (current, 30, 60, 90+ days), bank reference, trade references, credit decision (approved, conditional, declined), decision date, approving authority, and risk tier (low, medium, high, watch). Sourced from D&B Direct, internal AR aging reports, and credit committee decisions. Critical for staffing firms managing significant accounts receivable exposure — supports go/no-go decisions on new business, headcount expansion approvals, and credit hold enforcement during invoice generation.' .

ind:VendorDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all vendor-submitted and vendor-related documents stored and versioned within the MSP/VMS program. Captures document type (W-9, COI, NDA, MSA, rate agreement, diversity certificate, insurance policy, compliance attestation, executed SOW, training certificate, subcontractor agreement), document title, file reference/URL, upload date, uploaded by, document version, effective date, expiration date, document status (current, superseded, expired, archived), associated vendor ID, retention policy classification, and document category (legal, compliance, financial, operational). Provides a centralized document repository for vendor management teams who manage hundreds of documents per supplier. Supports document expiration alerting and version control. Distinct from compliance-specific status tracking (owned by vendor_compliance) — this product owns the physical document inventory, version history, and storage references, while vendor_compliance owns the compliance status determination and audit workflow that references these documents.' .

ind:StateComplianceRule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'State Compliance Rule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for state-specific and local jurisdiction compliance requirements that vary by geography and impact multi-state staffing operations. Captures state/locality, effective date, expiration date, requirement type (ban-the-box, pay transparency, salary history ban, state E-Verify mandate, state-specific drug testing restrictions, portable background check laws, paid sick leave mandate, predictive scheduling, wage theft prevention notice, state mini-WARN Act, independent contractor classification test variations such as ABC test vs. common law test), applicability criteria (employer size threshold, industry sector, worker type), penalty for non-compliance, enforcement agency, and source citation with URL. Drives jurisdiction-aware compliance enforcement for multi-state staffing operations. Distinct from compliance_requirement which owns federal regulations and client-specific contractual mandates.' .

ind:JobCategory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Category' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference entity defining standardized job categories, job families, and occupational classifications (SOC codes, O*NET) used to classify requisitions and match candidates' .

ind:JoborderApprovalWorkflow rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Joborder Approval Workflow' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the internal and client-side approval chain for new job orders and requisition modifications, capturing approver, approval date, status, and comments' .

ind:Referral rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Referral' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks candidate referrals from employees, placed workers, or external sources, capturing referrer identity, referred candidate, referral date, and referral bonus eligibility' .

ind:JobBoardIntegration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Board Integration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for job board and aggregator integrations (Indeed, LinkedIn, ZipRecruiter, CareerBuilder) tracking posting rules, API credentials, cost per posting, and performance metrics' .

ind:GlAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Gl Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Chart of Accounts master record defining every general ledger account used in the staffing enterprise. Captures account number, account name, account type (asset, liability, equity, revenue, expense), account class, normal balance (debit/credit), parent account for hierarchy rollup, cost center applicability, intercompany flag, consolidation account mapping, GAAP/IFRS classification, active status, and effective date range. SSOT for all GL account definitions used across journal entries, cost allocations, and financial reporting.' .

ind:CostCenter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Center' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Organizational cost center master record representing a financial accountability unit within the staffing enterprise. Captures cost center code, name, description, cost center type (branch, division, corporate, shared services), owning business unit, regional hierarchy, manager, budget owner, active status, and effective dates. Used to allocate revenues and expenses across branches, divisions, and service lines for internal P&L reporting and profitability analysis.' .

ind:JournalEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'General ledger journal entry header record representing a balanced accounting transaction posted to the staffing enterprise\'s general ledger. Captures journal entry number, journal date, posting date, period, fiscal year, journal type (standard, adjusting, reversing, accrual, intercompany), source system (payroll, billing, AP, AR), description, total debit amount, total credit amount, currency, exchange rate, preparer, approver, approval date, reversal flag, reversal date, and posting status. Core transactional record for all financial accounting activity.' .

ind:JournalEntryLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual debit or credit line within a general ledger journal entry. Captures line sequence number, GL account, cost center, department, project code, intercompany entity, debit amount, credit amount, functional currency amount, transaction currency amount, exchange rate, line description, tax code, and reconciliation status. Each journal entry must have balanced lines (total debits = total credits). Enables granular GL drill-down and account-level financial analysis.' .

ind:AccountingPeriod rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Accounting Period' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Fiscal accounting period master record defining the financial calendar for the staffing enterprise. Captures period number, period name, fiscal year, period start date, period end date, period type (monthly, quarterly, annual), period status (open, closed, locked, adjusting), close date, closed by, and associated fiscal calendar. Controls which periods are open for journal entry posting and drives financial reporting period alignment across AR, AP, payroll, and billing sub-ledgers.' .

ind:ArAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ar Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts receivable sub-ledger account master record representing the outstanding receivable balance owed by a client to the staffing firm. Captures client billing account reference, AR account number, current balance, aging buckets (current, 30, 60, 90, 90+ days), credit limit, payment terms (Net 30, Net 45, Net 60), currency, last payment date, last invoice date, collection status, dunning level, assigned collector, and account open/close dates. SSOT for client-level AR balance and aging within the finance domain.' .

ind:ArTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ar Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts receivable transactional record capturing every AR movement event for a client — invoice postings, payment applications, credit memo applications, adjustments, and write-offs. Captures transaction date, transaction type (invoice, payment, credit memo, debit memo, write-off, adjustment), source document reference (invoice_id, payment_id, credit_memo_id), transaction amount, applied amount, unapplied amount, currency, exchange rate, GL period, and posting status. Provides the complete AR activity ledger for client account reconciliation.' .

ind:ApAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable sub-ledger account master record representing the outstanding payable balance owed by the staffing firm to a vendor, supplier, or service provider. Captures vendor/supplier reference, AP account number, current balance, aging buckets, payment terms, preferred payment method (ACH, check, wire), currency, last payment date, last invoice date, 1099 reporting flag, tax ID, and account status. Manages the firm\'s obligations to third-party staffing suppliers, subcontractors, and service vendors within MSP/VMS programs.' .

ind:ApInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable invoice record representing a vendor or supplier bill received by the staffing firm for services rendered. Captures vendor reference, invoice number, invoice date, received date, due date, payment terms, invoice amount, tax amount, total amount, currency, GL period, cost center allocation, approval status, approver, approved date, payment status, payment date, and 3-way match status (PO, receipt, invoice). Covers vendor staffing supplier invoices, subcontractor bills, and third-party service provider charges within MSP programs.' .

ind:ApPayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Ap Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accounts payable payment disbursement record capturing each payment made by the staffing firm to a vendor or supplier. Captures payment date, payment method (ACH, check, wire transfer, virtual card), payment amount, currency, exchange rate, bank account, check number or ACH trace number, payment status (scheduled, issued, cleared, voided), void date, void reason, and associated AP invoices settled. Tracks the full disbursement lifecycle from payment scheduling through bank clearance for vendor and supplier payments.' .

ind:RevenueRecognitionEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Revenue Recognition Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Revenue recognition event record capturing the point-in-time recognition of staffing revenue in accordance with ASC 606 / IFRS 15. Captures recognition date, recognition method (time-and-materials, milestone, percentage-of-completion, fixed-fee), recognized revenue amount, deferred revenue amount, contract liability amount, performance obligation reference, placement or SOW engagement reference, GL period, cost center, and recognition status. Ensures revenue is recognized in the correct period as performance obligations are satisfied — critical for staffing firms with temp, contract, and SOW billing models.' .

ind:DeferredRevenue rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Deferred Revenue' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Deferred revenue liability record tracking revenue received or billed but not yet earned under ASC 606 / IFRS 15 for the staffing enterprise. Captures client reference, contract reference, deferred amount, recognition start date, recognition end date, recognition schedule type (straight-line, milestone, usage-based), recognized-to-date amount, remaining deferred balance, GL account, cost center, and period-end balance. Applies to retainer arrangements, prepaid staffing contracts, SOW fixed-fee engagements, and RPO program fees billed in advance.' .

ind:IntercompanyTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Intercompany Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Intercompany transaction record capturing financial activity between legal entities within the staffing enterprise group — including shared service charges, management fee allocations, intercompany loans, and cross-entity payroll funding. Captures originating entity, receiving entity, transaction type (charge, allocation, loan, dividend), transaction date, amount, currency, exchange rate, GL accounts on both sides, elimination flag, reconciliation status, and approval status. Essential for consolidated financial reporting and intercompany elimination during period-end close.' .

ind:Budget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual or periodic financial budget master record for the staffing enterprise. Captures budget name, budget version (original, revised, forecast), fiscal year, budget period, budget type (operating, capital, headcount), owning cost center or business unit, GL account, budgeted amount, currency, budget status (draft, approved, locked), approved by, approval date, and budget notes. Supports branch-level, division-level, and enterprise-level budget management for revenue, gross margin, SG&A, and headcount planning.' .

ind:BudgetLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line-item record within a financial budget, capturing the granular GL account and cost center level budget allocation. Captures budget reference, GL account, cost center, department, period (monthly/quarterly), budgeted amount, prior year actual amount, variance to prior year, budget notes, and last updated timestamp. Enables detailed budget-vs-actual variance analysis at the account and cost center level across branches, divisions, and service lines.' .

ind:BankAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bank Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Corporate bank account master record for all bank accounts maintained by the staffing enterprise. Captures bank name, bank routing number, account number (masked), account type (operating, payroll, trust, concentration), currency, legal entity owner, account status (active, dormant, closed), signatory list, overdraft limit, and associated GL cash account. Covers operating accounts, payroll funding accounts, client trust accounts, and concentration accounts used across the staffing firm\'s treasury operations.' .

ind:BankTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bank Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Bank statement transaction record capturing each debit and credit movement on a corporate bank account as reported by the bank. Captures bank account reference, transaction date, value date, transaction type (deposit, withdrawal, ACH credit, ACH debit, wire, check, fee, interest), transaction amount, currency, bank reference number, description, reconciliation status (unreconciled, matched, cleared), matched GL transaction reference, and reconciliation date. Drives the bank reconciliation process and cash position management.' .

ind:BankReconciliation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Bank Reconciliation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Bank reconciliation record capturing the period-end reconciliation of a corporate bank account balance to the GL cash account balance. Captures bank account reference, reconciliation period, statement date, bank statement ending balance, GL book balance, outstanding deposits-in-transit total, outstanding checks/payments total, bank errors, book errors, adjusted bank balance, adjusted book balance, reconciliation status (in-progress, reconciled, approved), preparer, reviewer, and completion date. Ensures cash integrity across all staffing firm bank accounts.' .

ind:PeriodCloseTask rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Period Close Task' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Financial period-end close task record tracking each step in the monthly, quarterly, and annual close process for the staffing enterprise. Captures task name, task type (accrual, reconciliation, journal entry, sub-ledger close, consolidation, reporting), assigned owner, due date, completion date, status (not started, in progress, completed, overdue, waived), dependency on prior tasks, close period reference, and sign-off notes. Manages the structured close checklist ensuring all accounting activities are completed before the period is locked.' .

ind:Accrual rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Accrual' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Accrual record capturing estimated expense or revenue amounts recorded in the general ledger before the actual invoice or cash transaction is received. Captures accrual type (payroll accrual, unbilled revenue, vendor accrual, bonus accrual, workers comp accrual), accrual date, GL period, GL account, cost center, accrual amount, currency, basis of estimate (hours × rate, percentage, fixed), source reference (assignment, pay period, contract), reversal date, reversal status, and preparer. Critical for staffing firms where payroll and billing cycles span period boundaries.' .

ind:TaxLiability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Liability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Corporate tax liability record tracking the staffing enterprise\'s tax obligations across federal, state, and local jurisdictions — separate from worker-level payroll tax (owned by payroll domain). Captures tax type (corporate income tax, sales tax, use tax, franchise tax, gross receipts tax), jurisdiction (federal, state, local), tax period, taxable base amount, tax rate, calculated tax amount, credits applied, net tax due, payment due date, filing due date, payment status, and filing reference. Covers the firm\'s own corporate tax obligations distinct from employer payroll tax.' .

ind:FixedAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Fixed Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Fixed asset master record for capital assets owned or leased by the staffing enterprise — including office equipment, leasehold improvements, furniture, vehicles, and technology infrastructure. Captures asset tag number, asset name, asset category, acquisition date, acquisition cost, useful life (months), depreciation method (straight-line, declining balance, MACRS), accumulated depreciation, net book value, salvage value, disposal date, disposal proceeds, gain/loss on disposal, physical location, assigned cost center, and asset status (active, disposed, fully depreciated). Supports capital expenditure tracking and depreciation scheduling.' .

ind:DepreciationSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Depreciation Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Depreciation schedule record capturing the period-by-period depreciation calculation for each fixed asset. Captures fixed asset reference, depreciation period, depreciation method, beginning net book value, depreciation expense for period, accumulated depreciation to date, ending net book value, GL account, cost center, and posting status. Drives the automated depreciation journal entries posted each accounting period and supports fixed asset sub-ledger reconciliation to the GL.' .

ind:LegalEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Legal Entity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legal entity master record for each incorporated business entity within the staffing enterprise group. Captures legal entity name, entity type (corporation, LLC, partnership, branch), EIN/tax ID, state of incorporation, registered address, functional currency, fiscal year end, consolidation group, parent entity, intercompany elimination flag, GAAP/IFRS reporting standard, active status, and formation/dissolution dates. SSOT for the corporate structure used in intercompany accounting, consolidated financial reporting, and regulatory filings.' .

ind:StaffProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Staff Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT master record for every internal employee at Staffing Hr — recruiters, account managers, sourcing specialists, operations staff, and corporate personnel. Captures core identity: legal name, preferred name, employee number, personal email, work email, work phone, mobile phone, date of birth, gender, SSN (masked), home address, emergency contact name, emergency contact phone, hire date, rehire flag, termination date, employment status (active, on leave, terminated), employment type (full-time, part-time, contract), FLSA classification, EEO job category, veteran status, disability status, and I-9 work authorization status. This is the authoritative identity record for all internal workforce — distinct from candidate.profile (external talent supply) and placement.assignment (worker deployments).' .

ind:JobTitle rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Title' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master defining all internal job titles and position classifications used across Staffing Hr. Captures title name, title code, job family (e.g., Recruiting, Account Management, Operations, Finance, IT), job level (individual contributor, team lead, manager, director, VP, C-suite), FLSA exemption status, EEO-1 job category code, O*NET SOC code, pay grade band, and whether the title is billable-facing or internal. Used to standardize job title taxonomy across HRIS, payroll, and performance systems.' .

ind:Department rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Department' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all internal organizational departments and cost center units within Staffing Hr. Captures department name, department code, division (Operations, Business Development, Finance, HR, IT, Legal, Compliance), parent department for hierarchy, department head employee reference, GL cost center code, physical office location, and active status. Enables org chart traversal, headcount reporting by department, and cost allocation to finance.cost_center.' .

ind:Team rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Team' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for internal delivery teams within Staffing Hr — recruiting pods, account management teams, MSP program teams, RPO delivery teams, and branch office teams. Captures team name, team type (recruiting, account management, MSP, RPO, operations, corporate), team lead employee reference, parent department, geographic market or vertical focus (e.g., Healthcare IT, Light Industrial Southeast), target headcount, and active status. Supports team-level performance tracking, recruiter assignment routing, and capacity planning.' .

ind:TeamMembership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Team Membership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association record linking an internal employee to a specific team, capturing the employee\'s role on the team, start date, end date, membership status (active, inactive), and whether the employee is the team lead. Supports historical team composition tracking, team roster queries, and org change auditing. Enables many-to-many team assignments where employees may serve on multiple teams (e.g., a recruiter supporting both a primary pod and a surge team).' .

ind:RoleAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Role Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the assignment of a specific job role, system access role, or functional responsibility to an internal employee. Tracks role name, role type (job role, system role, functional responsibility), assigned date, effective start date, effective end date, assignment status, and the authorizing manager. Supports RBAC (Role-Based Access Control) provisioning, recruiter desk assignments, account manager territory ownership, and compliance audit trails for system access reviews.' .

ind:Compensation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Compensation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the current and historical compensation structure for each internal employee. Captures compensation type (salary, hourly, draw-plus-commission, commission-only), base salary or hourly rate, pay frequency (weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, monthly), currency, effective date, end date, compensation band, pay grade, overtime eligibility, and the reason for the compensation record (new hire, merit increase, promotion, market adjustment, equity correction). SSOT for internal employee pay rates — distinct from payroll.pay_rate (contingent worker pay) and billing.bill_rate (client-facing rates).' .

ind:CommissionPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Commission Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the commission and incentive compensation plan assigned to a revenue-generating internal employee (recruiter, account manager, business development rep). Captures plan name, plan type (gross margin split, placement fee percentage, spread-based, hybrid), commission rate tiers, accelerator thresholds, draw amount (if applicable), draw recovery terms, plan effective date, plan end date, and the approving manager. Critical for recruiter and account manager incentive management in staffing firms where variable compensation drives behavior.' .

ind:CommissionEarning rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Commission Earning' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each individual commission earning event for an internal employee. Tracks the triggering event type (placement start, direct hire fee collected, temp-to-perm conversion, spread milestone), associated placement or billing reference, gross margin or fee amount used as the basis, commission rate applied, commission amount earned, pay period, payment status (pending, approved, paid, clawed back), and any adjustments for fall-offs or reversals. Enables recruiter and account manager commission statement generation and dispute resolution.' .

ind:PerformanceReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for formal performance review cycles conducted for internal employees. Captures review period (annual, semi-annual, quarterly, 90-day), review type (standard, probationary, PIP, promotion readiness), overall rating (e.g., Exceeds Expectations, Meets Expectations, Needs Improvement), review status (scheduled, in progress, completed, acknowledged), review date, reviewer employee reference, and whether the review triggered a compensation change or promotion. Supports talent management, succession planning, and PIP tracking.' .

ind:PerformanceGoal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Goal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing individual performance goals and OKRs set for an internal employee within a review period. Tracks goal title, goal description, goal category (revenue, activity, quality, development), target metric (e.g., placements per month, gross margin target, submittal-to-hire ratio), target value, actual value, measurement unit, goal weight (percentage of overall rating), goal status (draft, active, completed, cancelled), and alignment to team or company-level objectives. Enables MBO (Management by Objectives) tracking for recruiters and account managers.' .

ind:PipRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Pip Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Performance Improvement Plans (PIPs) issued to internal employees who are not meeting performance expectations. Captures PIP start date, PIP end date, improvement areas identified, specific measurable targets required, check-in frequency, PIP outcome (successfully completed, extended, terminated, resigned), HR business partner assigned, and whether legal review was conducted. Critical for HR compliance, documentation of progressive discipline, and wrongful termination risk mitigation in staffing firms.' .

ind:LeaveRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Leave Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for all internal employee leave requests and approved leave events. Captures leave type (PTO, sick, FMLA, parental, bereavement, jury duty, military, unpaid), request date, leave start date, leave end date, total days requested, approval status (pending, approved, denied, cancelled), approving manager, FMLA eligibility flag, intermittent leave flag, and return-to-work date. Distinct from timesheet.absence_record (which tracks contingent worker absences) — this entity owns internal staff leave management.' .

ind:BenefitEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Benefit Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record capturing an internal employee\'s enrollment in company-sponsored benefit plans. Tracks benefit plan type (medical, dental, vision, life insurance, STD, LTD, 401k, HSA, FSA, EAP), plan name, carrier name, coverage tier (employee only, employee + spouse, employee + children, family), enrollment effective date, termination date, employee contribution amount, employer contribution amount, enrollment source (open enrollment, new hire, qualifying life event), and dependent count. SSOT for internal employee benefits — distinct from any contingent worker benefit arrangements.' .

ind:OrgChangeEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Org Change Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Immutable transactional record capturing every organizational change event in an internal employee\'s lifecycle — promotions, demotions, lateral transfers, department changes, manager changes, title changes, location changes, employment type changes, and terminations. Captures event type, effective date, prior value, new value, change reason code, initiating manager, HR approver, and whether the change triggered a compensation adjustment. Serves as the authoritative audit trail for employee lifecycle changes, supporting HRIS reconciliation and compliance reporting.' .

ind:RecruiterDesk rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruiter Desk' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining a recruiter\'s operational desk configuration — the specific vertical, geography, job category, or client portfolio a recruiter is responsible for filling. Captures desk name, desk type (vertical-specific, geography-specific, client-dedicated, generalist), assigned recruiter, primary job categories covered, target industries, geographic territory, associated client accounts, desk open date, and active status. Enables recruiter workload management, req routing logic, and desk-level performance attribution in TempWorks and ATS systems.' .

ind:TerritoryAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Territory Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the assignment of a geographic territory, industry vertical, or named account portfolio to an internal account manager or business development representative. Tracks territory name, territory type (geographic, vertical, named account), assigned employee, effective start date, effective end date, assignment status, and whether the territory is exclusive. Supports sales territory management, account ownership routing, and commission attribution for account managers in staffing firms.' .

ind:InternalTraining rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Internal Training' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for internal training programs, certifications, and professional development courses available to Staffing Hr employees. Captures training name, training type (onboarding, compliance, product knowledge, sales skills, leadership development, DEI, safety), delivery method (in-person, virtual, LMS, on-the-job), duration hours, provider (internal, external vendor, LMS platform), required vs. elective flag, applicable job families, and recertification frequency. Distinct from credentialing.training_record (which tracks contingent worker training completions).' .

ind:TrainingCompletion rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Completion' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the completion or enrollment status of an internal employee in a specific training program. Tracks enrollment date, completion date, completion status (enrolled, in progress, completed, failed, expired), score or assessment result, certificate issued flag, certificate expiry date, and whether the completion satisfies a compliance requirement (e.g., annual harassment prevention training, FCRA training for recruiters). Enables compliance training tracking and L&D reporting for internal staff.' .

ind:HeadcountPosition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Headcount Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for approved internal headcount positions within Staffing Hr — the authorized slots in the org chart that may be filled, vacant, or frozen. Captures position title, position code, department, team, job level, FTE type (full-time, part-time), position status (filled, vacant, frozen, eliminated), budgeted flag, approved headcount date, and the requisition reference if the position is actively being recruited. Distinct from workforce.headcount_plan (which tracks contingent workforce planning) — this entity owns internal staff position management.' .

ind:InternalRequisition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Internal Requisition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for internal job requisitions opened to fill vacant headcount positions at Staffing Hr. Captures req number, req title, hiring department, hiring manager, target start date, req open date, req close date, req status (draft, open, on hold, filled, cancelled), number of openings, priority level, sourcing channel (internal transfer, external hire, referral), and whether the req is backfill or new headcount. Distinct from joborder.order_header (which tracks client-facing requisitions for contingent workers) — this entity owns internal talent acquisition demand.' .

ind:DisciplinaryAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Disciplinary Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for formal disciplinary actions issued to internal employees as part of progressive discipline processes. Captures action type (verbal warning, written warning, final written warning, suspension, termination), infraction category (attendance, performance, conduct, policy violation, compliance breach), incident date, action date, description of infraction, corrective action required, appeal status, HR reviewer, and whether legal counsel was involved. Supports HR compliance documentation, EEOC defense records, and wrongful termination risk management.' .

ind:Survey rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Survey' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing internal employee engagement survey responses and pulse check results. Tracks survey name, survey type (annual engagement, pulse, onboarding satisfaction, exit), survey period, response date, overall engagement score, eNPS (Employee Net Promoter Score), category scores (manager effectiveness, career development, compensation satisfaction, culture, work-life balance), response anonymization flag, and whether the employee consented to attribution. Supports internal retention analytics, manager effectiveness programs, and culture initiatives at Staffing Hr.' .

ind:OfficeLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Employee ;
    rdfs:label 'Office Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all physical Staffing Hr branch offices, corporate offices, and remote work hubs where internal employees are based. Captures location name, location code, address (street, city, state, zip, country), location type (branch office, corporate HQ, regional hub, remote), phone number, fax number, time zone, market region, branch manager employee reference, and active status. Supports employee location assignment, payroll tax jurisdiction determination, and branch-level performance reporting.' .

ind:BenchRoster rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Bench Roster' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Real-time roster of unassigned (bench) workers available for redeployment or new placement, tracking bench entry date, redeployment readiness, skill summary, and days on bench' .

ind:DispatchOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Dispatch Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Dispatch order record authorizing the deployment of a specific worker to a client site for a defined shift or work period' .

ind:WorkerSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Worker Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual worker shift schedule records capturing scheduled start/end times, shift type, work location, and assigned client for placed workers' .

ind:ScheduleException rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Schedule Exception' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of a scheduling exception or deviation from the planned worker schedule — including no-shows, late arrivals, early departures, and shift swaps' .

ind:ShiftTemplate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Shift Template' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reusable shift definition template capturing standard shift configurations — shift name, start/end times, shift duration, and break rules' .

ind:HeadcountPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Headcount Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Strategic headcount planning master record capturing FTE targets, headcount budgets, and workforce mix ratios for client programs and job categories' .

ind:DemandForecast rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Demand Forecast' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Time-series labor demand forecast records capturing projected worker demand by skill category, job family, client program, and time period' .

ind:CapacityPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Capacity Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Workforce supply capacity plan defining available worker capacity by skill pool, labor category, geography, and time period for fulfillment planning' .

ind:FteActuals rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Joborder ;
    rdfs:label 'Fte Actuals' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic snapshot of actual FTE counts by client program, labor category, and workforce mix type for tracking against headcount plan targets' .

ind:ManagedProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Managed Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a managed workforce program — RPO, MSP, or hybrid — operated on behalf of a client, capturing program scope, governance model, and SLA framework' .

ind:SlaBreachEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Sla Breach Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an SLA breach or near-miss event. Captures the breached SLA commitment, breach date, severity, root cause, and remediation actions' .

ind:PlacementRequirementCheck rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Placement Requirement Check' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the individual compliance requirement check results within a placement compliance gate-check process. Each record links one placement_compliance_check to one compliance_requirement and captures the specific check result, evidence, waiver status, and blocking determination for that requirement in the context of that placement. This is the operational record that compliance teams create, review, and manage to clear workers for assignment.. Existence Justification: In staffing compliance operations, each placement compliance gate-check evaluates the worker and placement against multiple compliance requirements (I-9, E-Verify, BGC, drug screen, credentials, safety training, client-specific mandates), and each compliance requirement is checked across thousands of placements. The business actively manages individual requirement check results with pass/fail/waived status, evidence references, waiver authorizations, and blocking determinations. This is not a derived correlation—it is the operational compliance checklist that humans create, review, approve, and use to block non-compliant placements from going active.' .

ind:AuditFinding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Finding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Finding relationship between compliance_audit and compliance_requirement. It captures each specific deficiency, gap, or non-compliance instance discovered during an audit that relates to a specific regulatory or contractual requirement. Each record links one compliance_audit to one compliance_requirement with attributes that describe the finding severity, remediation status, corrective actions, and evidence. Findings are actively managed business entities with their own lifecycle from identification through remediation to closure.. Existence Justification: In staffing compliance operations, audits systematically examine multiple regulatory and contractual requirements, and each requirement can be evaluated across many audits over time. Audit findings are actively managed business entities with their own lifecycle—compliance teams create finding records, assign owners, track remediation progress, manage corrective action plans, and report on finding trends. The business explicitly manages findings as distinct operational records, not as embedded attributes of audits.' .

ind:PackageRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Package Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the requirement relationship between credential_package and credential. It captures the specific rules and constraints that govern how each credential must be satisfied within the context of a specific credentialing package. Each record links one credential_package to one credential with attributes that define whether the credential is mandatory, verification requirements, expiry windows, renewal policies, and waiver rules for that specific package-credential combination.. Existence Justification: In staffing and recruitment operations, credential packages are reusable bundles that combine multiple credentials with package-specific rules. A single package (e.g., Healthcare Travel Nurse Package) requires multiple credentials (RN license, BLS, immunizations, background check), and a single credential (e.g., RN license) is required by multiple packages across different clients and verticals. Compliance teams actively configure and manage these package-credential relationships, setting mandatory/optional flags, verification levels, expiry windows, and waiver policies for each combination.' .

ind:AssignmentCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance fulfillment relationship between a worker assignment and a regulatory or client-specific compliance requirement. It captures the operational tracking of which requirements must be satisfied for each assignment, the completion status, verification methods, and re-verification schedules. Each record links one assignment to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific assignment-requirement pairing, enabling the business to enforce compliance gates, track waivers, and manage re-verification workflows.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each worker assignment must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (I-9 employment eligibility, background checks, drug screens, client-specific credentials, industry certifications, training mandates). Simultaneously, each compliance requirement applies to many assignments across different workers, clients, and time periods. The business actively manages the fulfillment status of each assignment-requirement pairing, tracking completion dates, verification methods, waivers, expiration dates, and re-verification schedules as operational data that belongs to neither the assignment nor the requirement alone.' .

ind:MsaCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Msa Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual credentialing requirements between credential and msa. It captures the specific credential compliance standards mandated by each Master Service Agreement. Each record links one credential type to one MSA with attributes that define how that credential must be verified, maintained, and enforced for placements under that contract.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each MSA specifies multiple credential requirements (licenses, certifications, background checks, drug screens, immunizations) that candidates must hold to be eligible for placement under that contract. Conversely, each credential type (e.g., RN license, OSHA 10, Hep B immunization) is required by multiple MSAs across different clients with varying enforcement rules. The business actively manages these requirements as \'MSA Credential Requirements\' or \'Contract Credentialing Standards\' with client-specific parameters for verification depth, expiry tolerances, and renewal lead times.' .

ind:SowCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Sow Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the credential requirements specified for a Statement of Work. It captures the project-specific credentialing rules that govern which credentials are mandatory, how they must be verified, and what exceptions or grace periods apply for workers assigned to this SOW. Each record links one credential to one SOW with attributes that define the enforcement rules, verification depth, timing requirements, and waiver policies specific to that engagement.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, a single SOW typically requires multiple credentials (e.g., RN license, BLS certification, TB test, background check) to ensure workers meet client and regulatory requirements, and each credential definition applies to many different SOWs across various clients and engagements. The business actively manages SOW-specific credential requirements during contract negotiation and SOW setup, defining which credentials are mandatory, how strictly they must be verified, what grace periods apply, and whether waivers are permitted—rules that vary by client risk tolerance, industry vertical, and regulatory context.' .

ind:ViolationBreach rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Violation Breach' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the breach relationship between a regulatory violation incident and the specific compliance requirements that were violated. Each record links one regulatory violation to one compliance requirement that was breached, capturing breach-specific attributes including severity assessment per requirement, financial penalty allocation per requirement, remediation status and timeline per requirement, affected population count per requirement, and breach narrative. Supports multi-requirement violation tracking, penalty allocation by requirement, remediation workflow per requirement, and regulatory reporting on repeat violations by requirement type.. Existence Justification: In staffing compliance operations, a single regulatory violation incident routinely breaches multiple compliance requirements simultaneously (e.g., an I-9 audit finding may violate federal I-9 completion requirements, state-specific verification requirements, and client-specific documentation mandates). Conversely, a specific compliance requirement (e.g., I-9 Employment Eligibility Verification) is violated across many separate incidents over time. The business actively manages this many-to-many relationship by tracking severity, penalties, remediation status, and affected populations per requirement within each violation, enabling requirement-level remediation workflows, penalty allocation, and regulatory reporting on repeat violations by requirement type.' .

ind:DeskSupplierAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Desk Supplier Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational allocation and access control between VMS-enrolled suppliers and internal recruiter desks. It captures how VMS supplier access is distributed across recruiting desks by job category, geography, or client segment. Each record links one enrolled supplier to one recruiter desk with allocation percentages, submission priorities, job category scope, and exclusive arrangement flags that exist only in the context of this desk-level supplier access relationship. Enables desk-level supplier management, req routing logic, and supplier utilization tracking.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations with VMS programs, suppliers are distributed across multiple internal recruiting desks based on job categories, geographies, and client segments, and each desk works with multiple enrolled suppliers simultaneously. The business actively manages desk-level supplier allocations with specific percentages, priority rankings, job category scopes, submission caps, and exclusive arrangements. This is an operational relationship that humans create, update, and monitor as part of supplier access control and req distribution workflows.' .

ind:SupplierComplianceObligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Compliance Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance obligation relationship between compliance requirements and suppliers in staffing operations. It captures which regulatory and contractual compliance requirements apply to which suppliers, tracking the compliance status, verification dates, expiration dates, waivers, and supporting documentation for each supplier-requirement pair. Each record links one compliance_requirement to one supplier with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific compliance obligation.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, compliance requirements apply to multiple suppliers (e.g., I-9 verification applies to all staffing agencies, insurance requirements apply to all IC suppliers), and each supplier must meet multiple compliance requirements (federal regulations, client-specific mandates, industry standards). The compliance team actively manages these supplier-requirement obligations as operational records, tracking compliance status, verification dates, waivers, and documentation for each unique supplier-requirement pair.' .

ind:OnboardingComplianceCheckpoint rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Onboarding Compliance Checkpoint' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the fulfillment tracking between compliance requirements and onboarding engagements. It captures the completion status, verification details, and waiver decisions for each compliance requirement within the context of a specific worker onboarding engagement. Each record links one compliance requirement to one onboarding engagement with attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each onboarding engagement must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (I-9, E-Verify, background checks, drug screens, client-specific mandates, federal contractor requirements), and each compliance requirement applies to many onboarding engagements across different workers and placements. The business actively manages compliance checkpoint completion as an operational process, tracking status, verification, waivers, and due dates for each requirement-engagement pair.' .

ind:CandidateCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Candidate Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the fulfillment status of compliance requirements by individual candidates in the staffing pipeline. It captures the operational tracking of which requirements each candidate has completed, when they were verified, their current status, and any waivers or exceptions granted. Each record links one candidate profile to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific candidate-requirement fulfillment relationship. Essential for onboarding clearance gates, placement eligibility determination, and regulatory audit readiness.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each candidate must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (I-9 employment eligibility, background checks, drug screens, industry certifications, client-specific training mandates), and each compliance requirement applies to many candidates across the talent pool. The business actively manages candidate compliance fulfillment as an operational process with dedicated compliance officers who track completion status, verification dates, expiration schedules, and waivers for each candidate-requirement pair. This is not a derived analytical correlation but a core operational workflow that gates onboarding clearance and placement eligibility.' .

ind:RateCardLine rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Rate Card Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the pricing line items within a client rate card, linking negotiated rates to specific job categories. Each record captures the bill rates, pay guidance, markup, and effective dates that apply when a specific job category is priced under a specific client rate card. This is the operational pricing matrix used daily in job order creation, candidate submittal pricing, and invoice generation.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, a single rate card negotiated with a client contains pricing for multiple job categories (e.g., Software Engineer, Project Manager, Business Analyst), and each job category appears across multiple client rate cards with different negotiated rates. The rate card is a pricing matrix, not a single-category document. Recruiters and account managers actively manage these rate card lines when creating job orders, pricing candidate submittals, and generating invoices.' .

ind:StateCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'State Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory requirement relationship between state compliance rules and credentials. It captures which credentials are mandated or recognized by specific state-level compliance regulations, including jurisdiction-specific enforcement details, effective periods, and penalty structures. Each record links one state compliance rule to one credential with attributes that exist only in the context of this state-specific regulatory requirement.. Existence Justification: In multi-state staffing operations, a single state compliance rule (e.g., California AB5 independent contractor classification) mandates multiple credentials (IC agreement, worker classification documentation, training certificates), and a single credential (e.g., OSHA 10 safety certification) satisfies requirements across multiple state rules (state-specific safety mandates, prevailing wage requirements, government contract rules). Compliance teams actively manage this matrix to ensure jurisdiction-aware placement eligibility and audit readiness.' .

ind:AssignmentSlaMeasurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment Sla Measurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the measurement record between assignment and sla. It captures the actual performance measurement of a specific SLA metric against a specific assignment during a defined measurement period. Each record links one assignment to one sla with the actual measured value, target comparison, breach determination, and measurement period boundaries that exist only in the context of this specific measurement event.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each worker assignment is measured against multiple SLA commitments (time-to-fill, quality-of-hire, retention rate, first-day no-show rate), and each SLA metric applies to many assignments across the client portfolio. The business actively manages SLA measurement as an operational process: for each assignment, performance is measured against applicable SLAs during defined measurement periods, actual values are compared to targets, breaches are flagged, and penalties/credits are calculated. This measurement data is used for client QBRs, scorecard reporting, and contract compliance tracking.' .

ind:AssignmentCredentialCompliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Assignment Credential Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance verification relationship between a worker assignment and a required credential. It captures the verification status, expiration tracking, and waiver management for each credential required for a specific assignment. Each record links one assignment to one credential with attributes that exist only in the context of ensuring placement compliance and regulatory adherence.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each assignment requires multiple credentials (professional licenses, safety certifications, immunizations, background checks, drug screens) and each credential type applies to many assignments over time. The business actively manages assignment-credential compliance as a distinct operational process, tracking verification dates, expiration monitoring, waiver approvals, and compliance status for each assignment-credential pair. This is not derivable from transaction history—it is an operational compliance management entity.' .

ind:BudgetAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation of budget amounts across organizational departments within Staffing Hr. It captures the distribution of financial budgets (operating, capital, headcount) to specific departments for a defined time period. Each record links one budget to one department with allocation-specific attributes including allocated amount, allocation percentage, effective dates, and budget category. This enables multi-department budget distribution, departmental cost tracking, and variance analysis by department.. Existence Justification: In staffing firms, budgets are allocated across multiple departments to distribute financial resources for different purposes (headcount, operations, technology, facilities). A single enterprise or division-level budget is split among multiple departments (recruiting, sales, operations, support), and each department receives allocations from multiple budget categories and fiscal periods. The business actively manages these allocations with specific amounts, percentages, effective dates, and approval workflows.' .

ind:ChecklistCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Checklist Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the requirement relationship between a task checklist template and a credential type. It captures the specific mandate, verification, and timing rules that govern when and how a credential must be verified as part of completing an onboarding or offboarding checklist. Each record links one credential to one task checklist with attributes that define the enforcement policy, verification level, timing offset, blocking behavior, and waiver eligibility for that specific checklist-credential combination.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, task checklist templates require multiple credentials (licenses, certifications, immunizations, background checks, drug screens) based on placement type, client requirements, and regulatory mandates. Each credential type applies to multiple checklist templates across different roles, geographies, and client accounts. The business actively manages these requirements as configuration rules, specifying for each checklist-credential pair whether the credential is mandatory, what verification level is required, timing offsets, blocking behavior, and waiver eligibility. This is a true operational M:N relationship recognized by the business as \'Checklist Credential Requirements\' or \'Credential Requirement Rules.\'' .

ind:Service rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Credentialing ;
    rdfs:label 'Service' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the service agreement between credential types and suppliers who provide verification, assessment, or compliance services for those credentials. It captures the operational catalog of which suppliers are approved to verify/assess which credential types, along with service-level agreements, pricing, turnaround times, and performance metrics. Each record links one credential type to one approved supplier with attributes that exist only in the context of this service relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, credential verification is outsourced to specialized suppliers who provide services like background checks, drug screening, license verification, and skills assessments. A single credential type (e.g., RN license, OSHA 10, TB immunization) can be verified by multiple approved suppliers, each with different pricing, turnaround times, and service quality. Conversely, a single supplier typically provides verification services for multiple credential types across their service portfolio. The business actively manages this service catalog, tracking SLAs, costs, performance ratings, and approval status for each supplier-credential combination.' .

ind:SupplierPackageQualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Package Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formal approval and qualification of a supplier to provide workers meeting a specific credential package. It captures the vendor approval process, compliance verification status, and package-specific vendor qualifications. Each record links one credential package to one supplier with attributes that exist only in the context of this qualification relationship, including approval status, verification dates, and expiration tracking.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, credential packages define standardized bundles of requirements (BGC, drug screens, licenses, training) for specific client programs or job categories, while suppliers are third-party staffing agencies and IC suppliers who provide workers. The business actively manages a Supplier Qualification Matrix where each supplier must be formally approved to provide workers meeting specific credential packages. One credential package (e.g., Healthcare Travel Nurse Package) can be fulfilled by multiple approved suppliers, and one supplier can be qualified to provide workers for multiple credential packages across different verticals or client programs. This is an operational relationship that humans create, audit, and revoke as part of vendor management and compliance workflows.' .

ind:OrientationAttendance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Onboarding ;
    rdfs:label 'Orientation Attendance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the attendance event between orientation_session and staff_profile. It captures the participation of internal staff members in orientation sessions, tracking their attendance status, completion, and assessment performance. Each record links one orientation_session to one staff_profile with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific attendance relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing and recruitment operations, orientation sessions are group training events where multiple internal staff members (recruiters, account managers, operations staff) attend, and each staff member participates in multiple orientation sessions over their employment lifecycle (initial onboarding, compliance refreshers, new client-specific orientations, role-change orientations). The business actively manages attendance records as operational entities, tracking registration, attendance status, completion, assessment scores, and certificate issuance for each staff-member-session combination.' .

ind:AuditSample rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Candidate ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Sample' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inclusion of a candidate profile in a compliance audit sample. It captures which candidates were selected for audit review, the selection criteria, findings specific to that candidate in that audit, and remediation status. Each record links one profile to one compliance_audit with attributes that exist only in the context of this audit sampling relationship. Critical for audit response, corrective action tracking, and regulatory compliance documentation.. Existence Justification: In staffing compliance operations, audits (I-9, OFCCP, wage/hour, client audits) routinely sample multiple candidate/worker records for review, and individual candidates may be included in multiple audits over time (e.g., an I-9 audit in Q1, an OFCCP audit in Q3, and a client compliance audit the following year). The business actively manages audit samples as operational records, tracking which candidates were selected, why they were selected, findings specific to each candidate in each audit, and remediation status for each candidate-audit combination.' .

ind:Allocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the financial allocation between a Statement of Work and a Cost Center. It captures how SOW delivery and costs are distributed across multiple organizational cost centers, enabling multi-location delivery tracking, shared services allocation, and accurate P&L attribution. Each record links one SOW to one cost center with allocation percentages, budget amounts, and actual costs that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, a single Statement of Work frequently spans multiple cost centers when delivery involves multiple branches, regions, or shared service units. Conversely, a cost center typically serves multiple active SOWs concurrently as part of normal operations. The business actively manages these allocations by tracking allocation percentages, budgeted amounts, and actual costs for each SOW-cost-center pairing to enable accurate P&L reporting and profitability analysis by organizational unit.' .

ind:ChecklistComplianceRule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Checklist Compliance Rule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational mapping between state compliance rules and task checklist templates. It captures which state-specific compliance requirements must be incorporated into which onboarding/offboarding checklists, with enforcement metadata that exists only in the context of this relationship. Each record links one state compliance rule to one task checklist template with attributes governing how that rule is enforced within that specific checklist context.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each state compliance rule (e.g., California Ban-the-Box, New York Salary Transparency) must be incorporated into multiple task checklist templates across different placement types, divisions, and client-specific scenarios. Conversely, each task checklist template must incorporate multiple state compliance rules based on the jurisdictions where workers will be placed. The business actively manages these mappings with enforcement metadata including effective dates, mandatory vs. optional status, task sequencing, SLA overrides, and enforcement priority that vary by checklist context.' .

ind:SubmittalComplianceCheck rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Recruitment ;
    rdfs:label 'Submittal Compliance Check' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance verification checkpoint between a candidate submittal and a specific compliance requirement. It captures the requirement-by-requirement compliance status for each submittal, including verification dates, waiver grants, blocking status, and documentation completeness. Each record links one submittal to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this verification relationship. Central to pre-placement compliance workflows and submittal clearance processes.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each candidate submittal must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (I-9 verification, background checks, drug screens, client-specific mandates, industry credentials), and each compliance requirement applies to many submittals across different candidates and job orders. The compliance team actively manages requirement-by-requirement verification status for each submittal, tracking verification dates, waivers, blocking status, and documentation completeness as part of the pre-placement clearance workflow.' .

ind:SupplierChecklistAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Checklist Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Assignment between supplier and task_checklist. It captures the configuration of which onboarding/offboarding checklists are required for which suppliers based on client program requirements, union status, healthcare credentialing needs, and client-mandated training. Each record links one supplier to one task_checklist with attributes that define when the assignment is effective, whether it has been approved, and any customization notes specific to that supplier-checklist combination.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, suppliers participate in multiple client programs with different compliance requirements, and each program may require multiple checklists (union vs non-union, healthcare credentialing, client-mandated training). One supplier uses multiple checklists across programs; one checklist template applies to multiple approved suppliers. The business actively manages these assignments as supplier program configurations change, client requirements evolve, and new compliance rules are introduced.' .

ind:SupplierOrientationAttendance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Vendor ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Orientation Attendance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the attendance relationship between suppliers and orientation sessions. It captures supplier participation in scheduled orientation events, tracking registration, attendance outcomes, cost allocation, and no-show patterns used for supplier performance scorecarding. Each record links one supplier to one orientation session with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific attendance event.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, suppliers send workers to multiple orientation sessions over time (different cohorts, different clients, different topics), and each orientation session hosts workers from multiple suppliers (multi-supplier MSP/VMS programs). The business actively manages supplier attendance records for cost allocation, billing, and supplier performance scorecarding based on no-show patterns.' .

ind:LocationComplianceMandate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Location Compliance Mandate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enforcement relationship between work locations and compliance requirements. It captures which federal, state, and client-specific compliance requirements are mandatory at each work location, along with site-specific enforcement parameters, audit history, and implementation status. Each record links one work location to one compliance requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this site-specific mandate.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, work locations are subject to multiple compliance requirements (OSHA postings, I-9 verification, state-specific rules, client contractual mandates, federal contractor obligations), and each compliance requirement applies to many work locations across the client portfolio. The compliance team actively manages which requirements are enforced at which sites, tracks site-specific enforcement levels (strict vs. advisory), conducts location-specific audits, and maintains site-specific implementation notes (e.g., \'Client requires bilingual OSHA postings\'). This is an operational enforcement relationship, not a derivable correlation.' .

ind:StaffComplianceCertification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Staff Compliance Certification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the certification relationship between compliance_requirement and staff_profile. It captures the assignment, completion, and ongoing tracking of mandatory compliance requirements for internal Staffing Hr employees. Each record links one compliance_requirement to one staff_profile with attributes that track certification status, completion dates, and recertification schedules for regulatory audit readiness.. Existence Justification: In staffing and HR operations, compliance requirements (I-9 training, OFCCP certification, privacy law training, background check training) are assigned to multiple internal staff members based on role, jurisdiction, and client contracts. Each staff member must complete multiple compliance requirements throughout their employment lifecycle. The business actively manages these certifications as operational records with completion tracking, recertification schedules, and audit trail requirements.' .

ind:ArrangementComplianceRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Arrangement Compliance Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the compliance obligation assignment between EOR arrangements and regulatory/contractual compliance requirements. It captures which party (Staffing Hr as EOR vs. client as co-employer) is responsible for satisfying each compliance requirement within the context of a specific EOR arrangement, along with compliance status tracking, audit schedules, and effective dates. Each record links one EOR arrangement to one compliance requirement with responsibility allocation and compliance monitoring attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing EOR operations, each EOR arrangement must satisfy multiple compliance requirements (I-9, E-Verify, EEOC reporting, OFCCP requirements, state-specific mandates, client-specific contractual requirements), and each compliance requirement applies to many EOR arrangements across different clients and worker populations. The business actively manages compliance obligation assignments, tracking which party (Staffing Hr as EOR vs. client as co-employer) is responsible for each requirement within each arrangement context, along with compliance status, audit schedules, and documentation. This is an operational compliance management process, not an analytical correlation.' .

ind:LocationBudgetAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Location Budget Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation of financial budgets to specific client work site locations in the staffing enterprise. It captures the distribution of operating, capital, and headcount budgets across physical and virtual work sites, enabling location-level financial planning, cost tracking, and variance analysis. Each record links one location to one budget with allocation percentage, effective period, and status attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, client locations require budget allocations for workforce planning and cost control. A single location can have multiple budgets allocated to it (operating budget for temp labor, capital budget for equipment, project-specific budgets for client programs), and a single enterprise or regional budget can be distributed across multiple locations with specific allocation percentages. Finance teams actively manage these allocations with effective dates, expiration dates, allocation percentages, and approval workflows.' .

ind:PayStubComplianceValidation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Payroll ;
    rdfs:label 'Pay Stub Compliance Validation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the validation event between pay_stub and compliance_requirement. It captures the compliance verification status for each pay stub against each applicable federal and client-specific requirement. Each record links one pay stub to one compliance requirement with validation outcome, timestamp, method, and exception handling attributes that exist only in the context of this compliance check.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, each pay stub must be validated against multiple compliance requirements (I-9 verification, wage/hour rules, tax withholding regulations, client-specific mandates), and each compliance requirement applies to many pay stubs across workers and pay periods. The compliance team actively manages validation records for audit defense, tracking which requirements were met, validation methods used, and exceptions granted for specific pay stub-requirement combinations.' .

ind:VendorCostCenterAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Contract ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Cost Center Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the allocation relationship between vendor agreements and cost centers within MSP/VMS-managed staffing programs. It captures the business rules governing which vendors are authorized to supply workers to which cost centers, including spend limits, allocation percentages, and effective date ranges. Each record links one vendor agreement to one cost center with attributes that exist only in the context of this allocation relationship. This enables multi-cost-center vendor agreements and multi-vendor cost center sourcing strategies.. Existence Justification: In MSP/VMS-managed staffing programs, vendor agreements are routinely allocated to multiple cost centers (e.g., IT, Finance, Operations branches), and each cost center sources workers from multiple approved vendors. The business actively manages these allocations with spend limits, allocation percentages, priority rankings, and effective date ranges. This is an operational relationship that procurement and MSP program managers create, monitor, and adjust based on vendor performance, budget constraints, and sourcing strategy.' .

ind:ProgramCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the credential requirements mandated by each VMS program. It captures which credentials are required for worker placement eligibility within a specific VMS program, along with program-specific verification standards and compliance rules. Each record links one VMS program to one credential with attributes that define the requirement context, mandatory status, verification level, and effective dates for that program-credential combination.. Existence Justification: VMS programs mandate multiple credentials for worker placement eligibility (background checks, drug screens, licenses, certifications, immunizations), and each credential type applies across multiple VMS programs with program-specific verification standards and mandatory status. The business actively manages these credential requirements as part of VMS program setup and compliance enforcement, tracking which credentials are required, at what verification level, and with what effective dates for each program.' .

ind:LocationCredentialRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Placement ;
    rdfs:label 'Location Credential Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the credential requirements mandated for a specific work location. It captures which credentials are required for workers to be placed at each location, with location-specific enforcement rules and effective dates. Each record links one work location to one credential with attributes that define the requirement parameters for that specific location-credential combination.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, work locations require multiple credentials (state licenses, facility-specific badges, OSHA certifications, immunizations, security clearances) and each credential type applies to multiple work locations across the client portfolio. The business actively manages location-credential requirement matrices to ensure placement compliance, with location-specific enforcement rules such as mandatory vs. preferred status, verification levels, and grace periods that vary by client site.' .

ind:ProgramComplianceRequirement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Client ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Compliance Requirement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the binding relationship between a managed workforce program and a compliance requirement. It captures program-specific enforcement rules, waiver status, effective dates, and client-specific thresholds that govern how each compliance requirement is applied within the context of a specific managed program. Each record links one managed_program to one compliance_requirement with attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship.. Existence Justification: In staffing operations, a single managed workforce program (MSP/RPO) must comply with multiple federal and client-specific compliance requirements (I-9, E-Verify, background checks, drug screening, client contractual mandates). Conversely, a single compliance requirement (e.g., I-9 verification) applies across multiple managed programs operated for different clients. The business actively manages this relationship by configuring program-specific enforcement rules, waivers, thresholds, and governance responsibilities for each program-requirement combination.' .

